20enum class OperandMode : uint32_t {
21 kNone = 0u,
22 // Immediate mode
23 kShift32Imm = 1u << 0,
24 kShift64Imm = 1u << 1,
25 kInt32Imm = 1u << 2,
26 kInt32Imm_Negate = 1u << 3,
27 kUint32Imm = 1u << 4,
28 kInt20Imm = 1u << 5,
29 kUint12Imm = 1u << 6,
30 // Instr format
31 kAllowRRR = 1u << 7,
32 kAllowRM = 1u << 8,
33 kAllowRI = 1u << 9,
34 kAllowRRI = 1u << 10,
35 kAllowRRM = 1u << 11,
36 // Useful combination
37 kAllowImmediate = kAllowRI | kAllowRRI,
38 kAllowMemoryOperand = kAllowRM | kAllowRRM,
39 kAllowDistinctOps = kAllowRRR | kAllowRRI | kAllowRRM,
40 kBitWiseCommonMode = kAllowRI,
41 kArithmeticCommonMode = kAllowRM | kAllowRI
42};
43
44using OperandModes = base::Flags<OperandMode, uint32_t>;
45DEFINE_OPERATORS_FOR_FLAGS(OperandModes)
46OperandModes immediateModeMask =
47 OperandMode::kShift32Imm | OperandMode::kShift64Imm |
48 OperandMode::kInt32Imm | OperandMode::kInt32Imm_Negate |
49 OperandMode::kUint32Imm | OperandMode::kInt20Imm;
50
51#define AndCommonMode \
52 ((OperandMode::kAllowRM | \
53 (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS) ? OperandMode::kAllowRRR \
54 : OperandMode::kNone)))
55#define And64OperandMode AndCommonMode
56#define Or64OperandMode And64OperandMode
57#define Xor64OperandMode And64OperandMode
58
59#define And32OperandMode \
60 (AndCommonMode | OperandMode::kAllowRI | OperandMode::kUint32Imm)
61#define Or32OperandMode And32OperandMode
62#define Xor32OperandMode And32OperandMode
63
64#define Shift32OperandMode \
65 ((OperandMode::kAllowRI | OperandMode::kShift64Imm | \
66 (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS) \
67 ? (OperandMode::kAllowRRR | OperandMode::kAllowRRI) \
68 : OperandMode::kNone)))
69
70#define Shift64OperandMode \
71 ((OperandMode::kAllowRI | OperandMode::kShift64Imm | \
72 OperandMode::kAllowRRR | OperandMode::kAllowRRI))
73
74#define AddOperandMode \
75 ((OperandMode::kArithmeticCommonMode | OperandMode::kInt32Imm | \
76 (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS) \
77 ? (OperandMode::kAllowRRR | OperandMode::kAllowRRI) \
78 : OperandMode::kArithmeticCommonMode)))
79#define SubOperandMode \
80 ((OperandMode::kArithmeticCommonMode | OperandMode::kInt32Imm_Negate | \
81 (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS) \
82 ? (OperandMode::kAllowRRR | OperandMode::kAllowRRI) \
83 : OperandMode::kArithmeticCommonMode)))
84#define MulOperandMode \
85 (OperandMode::kArithmeticCommonMode | OperandMode::kInt32Imm)

87template <typename Adapter>
88struct BaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacementMatch {
89 using node_t = typename Adapter::node_t;
90
91 node_t base = {};
92 node_t index = {};
93 int scale = 0;
94 int64_t displacement = 0;
95 DisplacementMode displacement_mode = kPositiveDisplacement;
96};
97
98std::optional<BaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacementMatch<TurboshaftAdapter>>
99TryMatchBaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacement64(
100 InstructionSelectorT<TurboshaftAdapter>* selector,
101 turboshaft::OpIndex node) {
102 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
103
104 // The BaseWithIndexAndDisplacementMatcher canonicalizes the order of
105 // displacements and scale factors that are used as inputs, so instead of
106 // enumerating all possible patterns by brute force, checking for node
107 // clusters using the following templates in the following order suffices
108 // to find all of the interesting cases (S = index * scale, B = base
109 // input, D = displacement input):
110 //
111 // (S + (B + D))
112 // (S + (B + B))
113 // (S + D)
114 // (S + B)
115 // ((S + D) + B)
116 // ((S + B) + D)
117 // ((B + D) + B)
118 // ((B + B) + D)
119 // (B + D)
120 // (B + B)
121 BaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacementMatch<TurboshaftAdapter> result;
122 result.displacement_mode = kPositiveDisplacement;
123
124 const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
125 if (const LoadOp* load = op.TryCast<LoadOp>()) {
126 result.base = load->base();
127 result.index = load->index().value_or_invalid();
128 result.scale = load->element_size_log2;
129 result.displacement = load->offset;
130 if (load->kind.tagged_base) result.displacement -= kHeapObjectTag;
131 return result;
132 } else if (const StoreOp* store = op.TryCast<StoreOp>()) {
133 result.base = store->base();
134 result.index = store->index().value_or_invalid();
135 result.scale = store->element_size_log2;
136 result.displacement = store->offset;
137 if (store->kind.tagged_base) result.displacement -= kHeapObjectTag;
138 return result;
139 } else if (op.Is<WordBinopOp>()) {
140 UNIMPLEMENTED();
141#ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
142 } else if (const Simd128LaneMemoryOp* lane_op =
143 op.TryCast<Simd128LaneMemoryOp>()) {
144 result.base = lane_op->base();
145 result.index = lane_op->index();
146 result.scale = 0;
147 result.displacement = 0;
148 if (lane_op->kind.tagged_base) result.displacement -= kHeapObjectTag;
149 return result;
150 } else if (const Simd128LoadTransformOp* load_transform =
151 op.TryCast<Simd128LoadTransformOp>()) {
152 result.base = load_transform->base();
153 result.index = load_transform->index();
154 DCHECK_EQ(load_transform->offset, 0);
155 result.scale = 0;
156 result.displacement = 0;
157 DCHECK(!load_transform->load_kind.tagged_base);
158 return result;
159#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
160 }
161 return std::nullopt;
162}

164// Adds S390-specific methods for generating operands.
165template <typename Adapter>
166class S390OperandGeneratorT final : public OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> {
167 public:
168 OPERAND_GENERATOR_T_BOILERPLATE(Adapter)
169
170 explicit S390OperandGeneratorT(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector)
171 : super(selector) {}
172
173 InstructionOperand UseOperand(node_t node, OperandModes mode) {
174 if (CanBeImmediate(node, mode)) {
175 return UseImmediate(node);
176 }
177 return UseRegister(node);
178 }
179
180 InstructionOperand UseAnyExceptImmediate(node_t node) {
181 if (this->is_integer_constant(node))
182 return UseRegister(node);
183 else
184 return this->Use(node);
185 }
186
187 int64_t GetImmediate(node_t node) {
188 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
189 turboshaft::ConstantOp* op =
190 this->turboshaft_graph()
191 ->Get(node)
192 .template TryCast<turboshaft::ConstantOp>();
193 switch (op->kind) {
194 case turboshaft::ConstantOp::Kind::kWord32:
195 return op->word32();
196 case turboshaft::ConstantOp::Kind::kWord64:
197 return op->word64();
198 default:
199 UNIMPLEMENTED();
200 }
201 } else {
202 if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kInt32Constant)
203 return OpParameter<int32_t>(node->op());
204 else if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kInt64Constant)
205 return OpParameter<int64_t>(node->op());
206 else
207 UNIMPLEMENTED();
208 }
209 }
210
211 bool CanBeImmediate(node_t node, OperandModes mode) {
212 if (!selector()->is_integer_constant(node)) return false;
213 int64_t value = selector()->integer_constant(node);
214 return CanBeImmediate(value, mode);
215 }
216
217 bool CanBeImmediate(int64_t value, OperandModes mode) {
218 if (mode & OperandMode::kShift32Imm)
219 return 0 <= value && value < 32;
220 else if (mode & OperandMode::kShift64Imm)
221 return 0 <= value && value < 64;
222 else if (mode & OperandMode::kInt32Imm)
223 return is_int32(value);
224 else if (mode & OperandMode::kInt32Imm_Negate)
225 return is_int32(-value);
226 else if (mode & OperandMode::kUint32Imm)
227 return is_uint32(value);
228 else if (mode & OperandMode::kInt20Imm)
229 return is_int20(value);
230 else if (mode & OperandMode::kUint12Imm)
231 return is_uint12(value);
232 else
233 return false;
234 }
235
236 bool CanBeMemoryOperand(InstructionCode opcode, node_t user, node_t input,
237 int effect_level) {
238 if (!this->IsLoadOrLoadImmutable(input)) return false;
239 if (!selector()->CanCover(user, input)) return false;
240 if (effect_level != selector()->GetEffectLevel(input)) {
241 return false;
242 }
243
244 MachineRepresentation rep =
245 this->load_view(input).loaded_rep().representation();
246 switch (opcode) {
247 case kS390_Cmp64:
248 case kS390_LoadAndTestWord64:
249 if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord64 ||
250 (!COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL && IsAnyTagged(rep))) {
251 DCHECK_EQ(ElementSizeInBits(rep), 64);
252 return true;
253 }
254 break;
255 case kS390_LoadAndTestWord32:
256 case kS390_Cmp32:
257 if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord32 ||
258 (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL && IsAnyCompressed(rep))) {
259 DCHECK_EQ(ElementSizeInBits(rep), 32);
260 return true;
261 }
262 break;
263 default:
264 break;
265 }
266 return false;
267 }
268
269 AddressingMode GenerateMemoryOperandInputs(
270 optional_node_t index, node_t base, int64_t displacement,
271 DisplacementMode displacement_mode, InstructionOperand inputs[],
272 size_t* input_count,
273 RegisterUseKind reg_kind = RegisterUseKind::kUseRegister) {
274 AddressingMode mode = kMode_MRI;
275 if (this->valid(base)) {
276 inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseRegister(base, reg_kind);
277 if (this->valid(index)) {
278 inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseRegister(this->value(index), reg_kind);
279 if (displacement != 0) {
280 inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseImmediate(
281 displacement_mode == kNegativeDisplacement ? -displacement
282 : displacement);
283 mode = kMode_MRRI;
284 } else {
285 mode = kMode_MRR;
286 }
287 } else {
288 if (displacement == 0) {
289 mode = kMode_MR;
290 } else {
291 inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseImmediate(
292 displacement_mode == kNegativeDisplacement ? -displacement
293 : displacement);
294 mode = kMode_MRI;
295 }
296 }
297 } else {
298 DCHECK(this->valid(index));
299 inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseRegister(this->value(index), reg_kind);
300 if (displacement != 0) {
301 inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseImmediate(
302 displacement_mode == kNegativeDisplacement ? -displacement
303 : displacement);
304 mode = kMode_MRI;
305 } else {
306 mode = kMode_MR;
307 }
308 }
309 return mode;
310 }
311
312 AddressingMode GenerateMemoryOperandInputs(
313 Node* index, Node* base, Node* displacement,
314 DisplacementMode displacement_mode, InstructionOperand inputs[],
315 size_t* input_count,
316 RegisterUseKind reg_kind = RegisterUseKind::kUseRegister) {
317 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
318 // Turboshaft is not using this overload.
319 UNREACHABLE();
320 } else {
321 int64_t displacement_value;
322 if (displacement == nullptr) {
323 displacement_value = 0;
324 } else if (displacement->opcode() == IrOpcode::kInt32Constant) {
325 displacement_value = OpParameter<int32_t>(displacement->op());
326 } else if (displacement->opcode() == IrOpcode::kInt64Constant) {
327 displacement_value = OpParameter<int64_t>(displacement->op());
328 } else {
329 UNREACHABLE();
330 }
331 return GenerateMemoryOperandInputs(index, base, displacement_value,
332 displacement_mode, inputs,
333 input_count);
334 }
335 }
336
337 AddressingMode GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(
338 typename Adapter::node_t operand, InstructionOperand inputs[],
339 size_t* input_count,
340 OperandModes immediate_mode = OperandMode::kInt20Imm) {
341 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
342 auto m =
343 TryMatchBaseWithScaledIndexAndDisplacement64(selector(), operand);
344 DCHECK(m.has_value());
345 if (TurboshaftAdapter::valid(m->base) &&
346 this->Get(m->base).template Is<turboshaft::LoadRootRegisterOp>()) {
347 DCHECK(!this->valid(m->index));
348 DCHECK_EQ(m->scale, 0);
349 inputs[(*input_count)++] =
350 UseImmediate(static_cast<int>(m->displacement));
351 return kMode_Root;
352 } else if (CanBeImmediate(m->displacement, immediate_mode)) {
353 DCHECK_EQ(m->scale, 0);
354 return GenerateMemoryOperandInputs(m->index, m->base, m->displacement,
355 m->displacement_mode, inputs,
356 input_count);
357 } else {
358 DCHECK_EQ(m->displacement, 0);
359 inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseRegister(m->base);
360 inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseRegister(m->index);
361 return kMode_MRR;
362 }
363
364 } else {
365 BaseWithIndexAndDisplacement64Matcher m(operand,
366 AddressOption::kAllowInputSwap);
367 DCHECK(m.matches());
368 if (m.base() != nullptr &&
369 m.base()->opcode() == IrOpcode::kLoadRootRegister) {
370 DCHECK_EQ(m.index(), nullptr);
371 DCHECK_EQ(m.scale(), 0);
372 inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseImmediate(m.displacement());
373 return kMode_Root;
374 } else if ((m.displacement() == nullptr ||
375 CanBeImmediate(m.displacement(), immediate_mode))) {
376 DCHECK_EQ(0, m.scale());
377 return GenerateMemoryOperandInputs(m.index(), m.base(), m.displacement(),
378 m.displacement_mode(), inputs,
379 input_count);
380 } else {
381 inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseRegister(operand->InputAt(0));
382 inputs[(*input_count)++] = UseRegister(operand->InputAt(1));
383 return kMode_MRR;
384 }
385 }
386 }
387
388 bool CanBeBetterLeftOperand(node_t node) const {
389 return !selector()->IsLive(node);
390 }
391
392 MachineRepresentation GetRepresentation(Node* node) {
393 return this->sequence()->GetRepresentation(
394 selector()->GetVirtualRegister(node));
395 }
396
397 bool Is64BitOperand(Node* node) {
398 return MachineRepresentation::kWord64 == GetRepresentation(node);
399 }
400};

404bool S390OpcodeOnlySupport12BitDisp(ArchOpcode opcode) {
405 switch (opcode) {
406 case kS390_AddFloat:
407 case kS390_AddDouble:
408 case kS390_CmpFloat:
409 case kS390_CmpDouble:
410 case kS390_Float32ToDouble:
411 return true;
412 default:
413 return false;
414 }
415}

417bool S390OpcodeOnlySupport12BitDisp(InstructionCode op) {
418 ArchOpcode opcode = ArchOpcodeField::decode(op);
419 return S390OpcodeOnlySupport12BitDisp(opcode);
420}

422#define OpcodeImmMode(op) \
423 (S390OpcodeOnlySupport12BitDisp(op) ? OperandMode::kUint12Imm \
424 : OperandMode::kInt20Imm)

426ArchOpcode SelectLoadOpcode(turboshaft::MemoryRepresentation loaded_rep,
427 turboshaft::RegisterRepresentation result_rep) {
428 // NOTE: The meaning of `loaded_rep` = `MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged()` is
429 // we are loading a compressed tagged field, while `result_rep` =
430 // `RegisterRepresentation::Tagged()` refers to an uncompressed tagged value.
431 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
432 switch (loaded_rep) {
433 case MemoryRepresentation::Int8():
434 DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
435 return kS390_LoadWordS8;
436 case MemoryRepresentation::Uint8():
437 DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
438 return kS390_LoadWordU8;
439 case MemoryRepresentation::Int16():
440 DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
441 return kS390_LoadWordS16;
442 case MemoryRepresentation::Uint16():
443 DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
444 return kS390_LoadWordU16;
445 case MemoryRepresentation::Int32():
446 case MemoryRepresentation::Uint32():
447 DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
448 return kS390_LoadWordU32;
449 case MemoryRepresentation::Int64():
450 case MemoryRepresentation::Uint64():
451 DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Word64());
452 return kS390_LoadWord64;
453 case MemoryRepresentation::Float16():
454 UNIMPLEMENTED();
455 case MemoryRepresentation::Float32():
456 DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Float32());
457 return kS390_LoadFloat32;
458 case MemoryRepresentation::Float64():
459 DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Float64());
460 return kS390_LoadDouble;
461#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
462 case MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged():
463 case MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer():
464 if (result_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Compressed()) {
465 return kS390_LoadWordS32;
466 }
467 DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged());
468 return kS390_LoadDecompressTagged;
469 case MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned():
470 if (result_rep == RegisterRepresentation::Compressed()) {
471 return kS390_LoadWordS32;
472 }
473 DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged());
474 return kS390_LoadDecompressTaggedSigned;
475#else
476 case MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged():
477 case MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer():
478 case MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned():
479 DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged());
480 return kS390_LoadWord64;
481#endif
482 case MemoryRepresentation::AnyUncompressedTagged():
483 case MemoryRepresentation::UncompressedTaggedPointer():
484 case MemoryRepresentation::UncompressedTaggedSigned():
485 DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged());
486 return kS390_LoadWord64;
487 case MemoryRepresentation::Simd128():
488 DCHECK_EQ(result_rep, RegisterRepresentation::Simd128());
489 return kS390_LoadSimd128;
490 case MemoryRepresentation::ProtectedPointer():
491 case MemoryRepresentation::IndirectPointer():
492 case MemoryRepresentation::SandboxedPointer():
493 case MemoryRepresentation::Simd256():
494 UNREACHABLE();
495 }
496}

498ArchOpcode SelectLoadOpcode(LoadRepresentation load_rep) {
499 ArchOpcode opcode;
500 switch (load_rep.representation()) {
501 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
502 opcode = kS390_LoadFloat32;
503 break;
504 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
505 opcode = kS390_LoadDouble;
506 break;
507 case MachineRepresentation::kBit: // Fall through.
508 case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
509 opcode = load_rep.IsSigned() ? kS390_LoadWordS8 : kS390_LoadWordU8;
510 break;
511 case MachineRepresentation::kWord16:
512 opcode = load_rep.IsSigned() ? kS390_LoadWordS16 : kS390_LoadWordU16;
513 break;
514 case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
515 opcode = kS390_LoadWordU32;
516 break;
517 case MachineRepresentation::kCompressedPointer: // Fall through.
518 case MachineRepresentation::kCompressed:
519 case MachineRepresentation::kIndirectPointer: // Fall through.
520 case MachineRepresentation::kSandboxedPointer: // Fall through.
521#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
522 opcode = kS390_LoadWordS32;
523 break;
524#else
525 UNREACHABLE();
526#endif
527#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
528 case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned:
529 opcode = kS390_LoadDecompressTaggedSigned;
530 break;
531 case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer:
532 opcode = kS390_LoadDecompressTagged;
533 break;
534 case MachineRepresentation::kTagged:
535 opcode = kS390_LoadDecompressTagged;
536 break;
537#else
538 case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned: // Fall through.
539 case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer: // Fall through.
540 case MachineRepresentation::kTagged: // Fall through.
541#endif
542 case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
543 opcode = kS390_LoadWord64;
544 break;
545 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
546 opcode = kS390_LoadSimd128;
547 break;
548 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat16:
549 UNIMPLEMENTED();
550 case MachineRepresentation::kProtectedPointer: // Fall through.
551 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd256: // Fall through.
552 case MachineRepresentation::kMapWord: // Fall through.
553 case MachineRepresentation::kNone:
554 default:
555 UNREACHABLE();
556 }
557 return opcode;
558}

560#define RESULT_IS_WORD32_LIST(V) \

562 V(BitcastFloat32ToInt32) \

598template <typename Adapter>
599bool ProduceWord32Result(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
600 typename Adapter::node_t node) {
601 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
602 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
603 const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
604 switch (op.opcode) {
605 case Opcode::kWordBinop: {
606 const auto& binop = op.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
607 if (binop.rep != WordRepresentation::Word32()) return false;
608 return binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kAdd ||
609 binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kSub ||
610 binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kMul ||
611 binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kSignedDiv ||
612 binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kUnsignedDiv ||
613 binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kSignedMod ||
614 binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kUnsignedMod ||
615 binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kBitwiseAnd ||
616 binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kBitwiseOr ||
617 binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kBitwiseXor ||
618 binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kSignedMulOverflownBits ||
619 binop.kind == WordBinopOp::Kind::kUnsignedMulOverflownBits;
620 }
621 case Opcode::kWordUnary: {
622 const auto& unop = op.Cast<WordUnaryOp>();
623 if (unop.rep != WordRepresentation::Word32()) return false;
624 return unop.kind == WordUnaryOp::Kind::kCountLeadingZeros ||
625 unop.kind == WordUnaryOp::Kind::kPopCount ||
626 unop.kind == WordUnaryOp::Kind::kSignExtend8 ||
627 unop.kind == WordUnaryOp::Kind::kSignExtend16;
628 }
629 case Opcode::kChange: {
630 const auto& changeop = op.Cast<ChangeOp>();
631 switch (changeop.kind) {
632 // Float64ExtractLowWord32
633 // Float64ExtractHighWord32
634 case ChangeOp::Kind::kExtractLowHalf:
635 case ChangeOp::Kind::kExtractHighHalf:
636 CHECK_EQ(changeop.from, FloatRepresentation::Float64());
637 CHECK_EQ(changeop.to, WordRepresentation::Word32());
638 return true;
639 // BitcastFloat32ToInt32
640 case ChangeOp::Kind::kBitcast:
641 return changeop.from == FloatRepresentation::Float32() &&
642 changeop.to == WordRepresentation::Word32();
643 case ChangeOp::Kind::kSignedFloatTruncateOverflowToMin:
644 case ChangeOp::Kind::kUnsignedFloatTruncateOverflowToMin:
645 // RoundFloat64ToInt32
646 // ChangeFloat64ToInt32
647 // TruncateFloat64ToUint32
648 // ChangeFloat64ToUint32
649 if (changeop.from == FloatRepresentation::Float64() &&
650 changeop.to == WordRepresentation::Word32()) {
651 return true;
652 }
653 // TruncateFloat32ToInt32
654 // TruncateFloat32ToUint32
655 if (changeop.from == FloatRepresentation::Float32() &&
656 changeop.to == WordRepresentation::Word32()) {
657 return true;
658 }
659 return false;
660 default:
661 return false;
662 }
663 return false;
664 }
665 case Opcode::kShift: {
666 const auto& shift = op.Cast<ShiftOp>();
667 if (shift.rep != WordRepresentation::Word32()) return false;
668 return shift.kind == ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftRightArithmetic ||
669 shift.kind == ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftRightLogical ||
670 shift.kind ==
671 ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftRightArithmeticShiftOutZeros ||
672 shift.kind == ShiftOp::Kind::kShiftLeft ||
673 shift.kind == ShiftOp::Kind::kRotateRight;
674 }
675 case Opcode::kOverflowCheckedBinop: {
676 const auto& ovfbinop = op.Cast<OverflowCheckedBinopOp>();
677 if (ovfbinop.rep != WordRepresentation::Word32()) return false;
678 return ovfbinop.kind == OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedAdd ||
679 ovfbinop.kind == OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedSub ||
680 ovfbinop.kind == OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedMul;
681 }
682 case Opcode::kLoad: {
683 LoadRepresentation load_rep = selector->load_view(node).loaded_rep();
684 MachineRepresentation rep = load_rep.representation();
685 switch (rep) {
686 case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
687 return true;
688 case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
689 if (load_rep.IsSigned())
690 return false;
691 else
692 return true;
693 default:
694 return false;
695 }
696 }
697 default:
698 return false;
699 }
700
701 } else {
702 switch (node->opcode()) {
703#define VISITOR(name) case IrOpcode::k##name:
704 RESULT_IS_WORD32_LIST(VISITOR)
705#undef VISITOR
706 return true;
707 // TODO(john.yan): consider the following case to be valid
708 // case IrOpcode::kWord32Equal:
709 // case IrOpcode::kInt32LessThan:
710 // case IrOpcode::kInt32LessThanOrEqual:
711 // case IrOpcode::kUint32LessThan:
712 // case IrOpcode::kUint32LessThanOrEqual:
713 // case IrOpcode::kUint32MulHigh:
714 // // These 32-bit operations implicitly zero-extend to 64-bit on x64, so
715 // the
716 // // zero-extension is a no-op.
717 // return true;
718 // case IrOpcode::kProjection: {
719 // Node* const value = node->InputAt(0);
720 // switch (value->opcode()) {
721 // case IrOpcode::kInt32AddWithOverflow:
722 // case IrOpcode::kInt32SubWithOverflow:
723 // case IrOpcode::kInt32MulWithOverflow:
724 // return true;
725 // default:
726 // return false;
727 // }
728 // }
729 case IrOpcode::kLoad:
730 case IrOpcode::kLoadImmutable: {
731 LoadRepresentation load_rep = LoadRepresentationOf(node->op());
732 switch (load_rep.representation()) {
733 case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
734 return true;
735 case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
736 if (load_rep.IsSigned())
737 return false;
738 else
739 return true;
740 default:
741 return false;
742 }
743 }
744 default:
745 return false;
746 }
747 }
748}

751static inline bool DoZeroExtForResult(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
752 typename Adapter::node_t node) {
753 return ProduceWord32Result<Adapter>(selector, node);
754}

761template <typename Adapter>
762void VisitTryTruncateDouble(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
763 ArchOpcode opcode, typename Adapter::node_t node) {
764 using node_t = typename Adapter::node_t;
765 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
766 InstructionOperand inputs[] = {g.UseRegister(selector->input_at(node, 0))};
767 InstructionOperand outputs[2];
768 size_t output_count = 0;
769 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
770
771 node_t success_output = selector->FindProjection(node, 1);
772 if (selector->valid(success_output)) {
773 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsRegister(success_output);
774 }
775
776 selector->Emit(opcode, output_count, outputs, 1, inputs);
777}

779template <class CanCombineWithLoad>
780void GenerateRightOperands(InstructionSelectorT<TurboshaftAdapter>* selector,
781 typename TurboshaftAdapter::node_t node,
782 typename TurboshaftAdapter::node_t right,
783 InstructionCode* opcode, OperandModes* operand_mode,
784 InstructionOperand* inputs, size_t* input_count,
785 CanCombineWithLoad canCombineWithLoad) {
786 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
787 S390OperandGeneratorT<TurboshaftAdapter> g(selector);
788
789 if ((*operand_mode & OperandMode::kAllowImmediate) &&
790 g.CanBeImmediate(right, *operand_mode)) {
791 inputs[(*input_count)++] = g.UseImmediate(right);
792 // Can only be RI or RRI
793 *operand_mode &= OperandMode::kAllowImmediate;
794 } else if (*operand_mode & OperandMode::kAllowMemoryOperand) {
795 const Operation& right_op = selector->Get(right);
796 if (right_op.Is<LoadOp>() && selector->CanCover(node, right) &&
797 canCombineWithLoad(
798 SelectLoadOpcode(selector->load_view(right).ts_loaded_rep(),
799 selector->load_view(right).ts_result_rep()))) {
800 AddressingMode mode =
801 g.GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(right, inputs, input_count);
802 *opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(mode);
803 *operand_mode &= ~OperandMode::kAllowImmediate;
804 if (*operand_mode & OperandMode::kAllowRM)
805 *operand_mode &= ~OperandMode::kAllowDistinctOps;
806 } else if (*operand_mode & OperandMode::kAllowRM) {
807 DCHECK(!(*operand_mode & OperandMode::kAllowRRM));
808 inputs[(*input_count)++] = g.UseAnyExceptImmediate(right);
809 // Can not be Immediate
810 *operand_mode &=
811 ~OperandMode::kAllowImmediate & ~OperandMode::kAllowDistinctOps;
812 } else if (*operand_mode & OperandMode::kAllowRRM) {
813 DCHECK(!(*operand_mode & OperandMode::kAllowRM));
814 inputs[(*input_count)++] = g.UseAnyExceptImmediate(right);
815 // Can not be Immediate
816 *operand_mode &= ~OperandMode::kAllowImmediate;
817 } else {
818 UNREACHABLE();
819 }
820 } else {
821 inputs[(*input_count)++] = g.UseRegister(right);
822 // Can only be RR or RRR
823 *operand_mode &= OperandMode::kAllowRRR;
824 }
825}

827template <typename Adapter, class CanCombineWithLoad>
828void GenerateRightOperands(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
829 typename Adapter::node_t node,
830 typename Adapter::node_t right,
831 InstructionCode* opcode, OperandModes* operand_mode,
832 InstructionOperand* inputs, size_t* input_count,
833 CanCombineWithLoad canCombineWithLoad) {
834 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
835
836 if ((*operand_mode & OperandMode::kAllowImmediate) &&
837 g.CanBeImmediate(right, *operand_mode)) {
838 inputs[(*input_count)++] = g.UseImmediate(right);
839 // Can only be RI or RRI
840 *operand_mode &= OperandMode::kAllowImmediate;
841 } else if (*operand_mode & OperandMode::kAllowMemoryOperand) {
842 NodeMatcher mright(right);
843 if (mright.IsLoad() && selector->CanCover(node, right) &&
844 canCombineWithLoad(
845 SelectLoadOpcode(LoadRepresentationOf(right->op())))) {
846 AddressingMode mode = g.GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(
847 right, inputs, input_count, OpcodeImmMode(*opcode));
848 *opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(mode);
849 *operand_mode &= ~OperandMode::kAllowImmediate;
850 if (*operand_mode & OperandMode::kAllowRM)
851 *operand_mode &= ~OperandMode::kAllowDistinctOps;
852 } else if (*operand_mode & OperandMode::kAllowRM) {
853 DCHECK(!(*operand_mode & OperandMode::kAllowRRM));
854 inputs[(*input_count)++] = g.UseAnyExceptImmediate(right);
855 // Can not be Immediate
856 *operand_mode &=
857 ~OperandMode::kAllowImmediate & ~OperandMode::kAllowDistinctOps;
858 } else if (*operand_mode & OperandMode::kAllowRRM) {
859 DCHECK(!(*operand_mode & OperandMode::kAllowRM));
860 inputs[(*input_count)++] = g.UseAnyExceptImmediate(right);
861 // Can not be Immediate
862 *operand_mode &= ~OperandMode::kAllowImmediate;
863 } else {
864 UNREACHABLE();
865 }
866 } else {
867 inputs[(*input_count)++] = g.UseRegister(right);
868 // Can only be RR or RRR
869 *operand_mode &= OperandMode::kAllowRRR;
870 }
871}

873template <typename Adapter, class CanCombineWithLoad>
874void GenerateBinOpOperands(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
875 typename Adapter::node_t node,
876 typename Adapter::node_t left,
877 typename Adapter::node_t right,
878 InstructionCode* opcode, OperandModes* operand_mode,
879 InstructionOperand* inputs, size_t* input_count,
880 CanCombineWithLoad canCombineWithLoad) {
881 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
882 // left is always register
883 InstructionOperand const left_input = g.UseRegister(left);
884 inputs[(*input_count)++] = left_input;
885
886 if (left == right) {
887 inputs[(*input_count)++] = left_input;
888 // Can only be RR or RRR
889 *operand_mode &= OperandMode::kAllowRRR;
890 } else {
891 GenerateRightOperands(selector, node, right, opcode, operand_mode, inputs,
892 input_count, canCombineWithLoad);
893 }
894}

896template <typename Adapter, class CanCombineWithLoad>
897void VisitUnaryOp(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,

902template <typename Adapter, class CanCombineWithLoad>
903void VisitBinOp(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
904 typename Adapter::node_t node, InstructionCode opcode,
905 OperandModes operand_mode, FlagsContinuationT<Adapter>* cont,
906 CanCombineWithLoad canCombineWithLoad);
907
908// Generate The following variations:
909// VisitWord32UnaryOp, VisitWord32BinOp,
910// VisitWord64UnaryOp, VisitWord64BinOp,
911// VisitFloat32UnaryOp, VisitFloat32BinOp,
912// VisitFloat64UnaryOp, VisitFloat64BinOp
913#define VISIT_OP_LIST_32(V) \
914 V(Word32, Unary, [](ArchOpcode opcode) { \
915 return opcode == kS390_LoadWordS32 || opcode == kS390_LoadWordU32; \
916 }) \
917 V(Word64, Unary, \
918 [](ArchOpcode opcode) { return opcode == kS390_LoadWord64; }) \
919 V(Float32, Unary, \
920 [](ArchOpcode opcode) { return opcode == kS390_LoadFloat32; }) \
921 V(Float64, Unary, \
922 [](ArchOpcode opcode) { return opcode == kS390_LoadDouble; }) \
923 V(Word32, Bin, [](ArchOpcode opcode) { \
924 return opcode == kS390_LoadWordS32 || opcode == kS390_LoadWordU32; \
925 }) \
926 V(Float32, Bin, \
927 [](ArchOpcode opcode) { return opcode == kS390_LoadFloat32; }) \
928 V(Float64, Bin, [](ArchOpcode opcode) { return opcode == kS390_LoadDouble; })
929
930#define VISIT_OP_LIST(V) \
931 VISIT_OP_LIST_32(V) \
932 V(Word64, Bin, [](ArchOpcode opcode) { return opcode == kS390_LoadWord64; })
933
934#define DECLARE_VISIT_HELPER_FUNCTIONS(type1, type2, canCombineWithLoad) \
935 template <typename Adapter> \
936 static inline void Visit##type1##type2##Op( \
937 InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector, typename Adapter::node_t node, \
938 InstructionCode opcode, OperandModes operand_mode, \
939 FlagsContinuationT<Adapter>* cont) { \
940 Visit##type2##Op(selector, node, opcode, operand_mode, cont, \
941 canCombineWithLoad); \
942 } \
943 template <typename Adapter> \
944 static inline void Visit##type1##type2##Op( \
945 InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector, typename Adapter::node_t node, \
946 InstructionCode opcode, OperandModes operand_mode) { \
947 FlagsContinuationT<Adapter> cont; \
948 Visit##type1##type2##Op(selector, node, opcode, operand_mode, &cont); \
949 }
950VISIT_OP_LIST(DECLARE_VISIT_HELPER_FUNCTIONS)
951#undef DECLARE_VISIT_HELPER_FUNCTIONS
952#undef VISIT_OP_LIST_32
953#undef VISIT_OP_LIST
954
955template <typename Adapter, class CanCombineWithLoad>
956void VisitUnaryOp(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
957 typename Adapter::node_t node, InstructionCode opcode,
958 OperandModes operand_mode, FlagsContinuationT<Adapter>* cont,
959 CanCombineWithLoad canCombineWithLoad) {
960 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
961 using node_t = typename Adapter::node_t;
962 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
963 InstructionOperand inputs[8];
964 size_t input_count = 0;
965 InstructionOperand outputs[2];
966 size_t output_count = 0;
967 node_t input = selector->input_at(node, 0);
968
969 GenerateRightOperands(selector, node, input, &opcode, &operand_mode, inputs,
970 &input_count, canCombineWithLoad);
971
972 bool input_is_word32 = ProduceWord32Result<Adapter>(selector, input);
973
974 bool doZeroExt = DoZeroExtForResult<Adapter>(selector, node);
975 bool canEliminateZeroExt = input_is_word32;
976
977 if (doZeroExt) {
978 // Add zero-ext indication
979 inputs[input_count++] = g.TempImmediate(!canEliminateZeroExt);
980 }
981
982 if (!cont->IsDeoptimize()) {
983 // If we can deoptimize as a result of the binop, we need to make sure
984 // that the deopt inputs are not overwritten by the binop result. One way
985 // to achieve that is to declare the output register as same-as-first.
986 if (doZeroExt && canEliminateZeroExt) {
987 // we have to make sure result and left use the same register
988 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineSameAsFirst(node);
989 } else {
990 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
991 }
992 } else {
993 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineSameAsFirst(node);
994 }
995
996 DCHECK_NE(0u, input_count);
997 DCHECK_NE(0u, output_count);
998 DCHECK_GE(arraysize(inputs), input_count);
999 DCHECK_GE(arraysize(outputs), output_count);
1000
1001 selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, output_count, outputs, input_count,
1002 inputs, cont);
1003}

1005template <typename Adapter, class CanCombineWithLoad>
1006void VisitBinOp(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
1007 typename Adapter::node_t node, InstructionCode opcode,
1008 OperandModes operand_mode, FlagsContinuationT<Adapter>* cont,
1009 CanCombineWithLoad canCombineWithLoad) {
1010 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
1011 using node_t = typename Adapter::node_t;
1012 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
1013 node_t left = selector->input_at(node, 0);
1014 node_t right = selector->input_at(node, 1);
1015 InstructionOperand inputs[8];
1016 size_t input_count = 0;
1017 InstructionOperand outputs[2];
1018 size_t output_count = 0;
1019
1020 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
1021 const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
1022 if (op.TryCast<WordBinopOp>() &&
1023 WordBinopOp::IsCommutative(
1024 selector->Get(node).template Cast<WordBinopOp>().kind) &&
1025 !g.CanBeImmediate(right, operand_mode) &&
1026 (g.CanBeBetterLeftOperand(right))) {
1027 std::swap(left, right);
1028 }
1029 } else {
1030 if (node->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kCommutative) &&
1031 !g.CanBeImmediate(right, operand_mode) &&
1032 (g.CanBeBetterLeftOperand(right))) {
1033 std::swap(left, right);
1034 }
1035 }
1036
1037 GenerateBinOpOperands(selector, node, left, right, &opcode, &operand_mode,
1038 inputs, &input_count, canCombineWithLoad);
1039
1040 bool left_is_word32 = ProduceWord32Result<Adapter>(selector, left);
1041
1042 bool doZeroExt = DoZeroExtForResult<Adapter>(selector, node);
1043 bool canEliminateZeroExt = left_is_word32;
1044
1045 if (doZeroExt) {
1046 // Add zero-ext indication
1047 inputs[input_count++] = g.TempImmediate(!canEliminateZeroExt);
1048 }
1049
1050 if ((operand_mode & OperandMode::kAllowDistinctOps) &&
1051 // If we can deoptimize as a result of the binop, we need to make sure
1052 // that the deopt inputs are not overwritten by the binop result. One way
1053 // to achieve that is to declare the output register as same-as-first.
1054 !cont->IsDeoptimize()) {
1055 if (doZeroExt && canEliminateZeroExt) {
1056 // we have to make sure result and left use the same register
1057 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineSameAsFirst(node);
1058 } else {
1059 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
1060 }
1061 } else {
1062 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineSameAsFirst(node);
1063 }
1064
1065 DCHECK_NE(0u, input_count);
1066 DCHECK_NE(0u, output_count);
1067 DCHECK_GE(arraysize(inputs), input_count);
1068 DCHECK_GE(arraysize(outputs), output_count);
1069
1070 selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, output_count, outputs, input_count,
1071 inputs, cont);
1072}

1127
1128static void VisitGeneralStore(
1129 InstructionSelectorT<TurboshaftAdapter>* selector,
1130 typename TurboshaftAdapter::node_t node, MachineRepresentation rep,
1131 WriteBarrierKind write_barrier_kind = kNoWriteBarrier) {
1132 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
1133 using node_t = TurboshaftAdapter::node_t;
1134 using optional_node_t = TurboshaftAdapter::optional_node_t;
1135 S390OperandGeneratorT<TurboshaftAdapter> g(selector);
1136
1137 auto store_view = selector->store_view(node);
1138 DCHECK_EQ(store_view.element_size_log2(), 0);
1139
1140 node_t base = store_view.base();
1141 optional_node_t index = store_view.index();
1142 node_t value = store_view.value();
1143 int32_t displacement = store_view.displacement();
1144
1145 if (write_barrier_kind != kNoWriteBarrier &&
1146 !v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) {
1147 DCHECK(CanBeTaggedOrCompressedPointer(rep));
1148 // Uncompressed stores should not happen if we need a write barrier.
1149 CHECK((store_view.ts_stored_rep() !=
1150 MemoryRepresentation::AnyUncompressedTagged()) &&
1151 (store_view.ts_stored_rep() !=
1152 MemoryRepresentation::UncompressedTaggedPointer()) &&
1153 (store_view.ts_stored_rep() !=
1154 MemoryRepresentation::UncompressedTaggedPointer()));
1155 AddressingMode addressing_mode;
1156 InstructionOperand inputs[4];
1157 size_t input_count = 0;
1158 addressing_mode = g.GenerateMemoryOperandInputs(
1159 index, base, displacement, DisplacementMode::kPositiveDisplacement,
1160 inputs, &input_count,
1161 S390OperandGeneratorT<
1162 TurboshaftAdapter>::RegisterUseKind::kUseUniqueRegister);
1163 DCHECK_LT(input_count, 4);
1164 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(value);
1165 RecordWriteMode record_write_mode =
1166 WriteBarrierKindToRecordWriteMode(write_barrier_kind);
1167 InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister(), g.TempRegister()};
1168 size_t const temp_count = arraysize(temps);
1169 InstructionCode code = kArchStoreWithWriteBarrier;
1170 code |= AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode);
1171 code |= RecordWriteModeField::encode(record_write_mode);
1172 selector->Emit(code, 0, nullptr, input_count, inputs, temp_count, temps);
1173 } else {
1174 ArchOpcode opcode;
1175
1176 switch (store_view.ts_stored_rep()) {
1177 case MemoryRepresentation::Int8():
1178 case MemoryRepresentation::Uint8():
1179 opcode = kS390_StoreWord8;
1180 break;
1181 case MemoryRepresentation::Int16():
1182 case MemoryRepresentation::Uint16():
1183 opcode = kS390_StoreWord16;
1184 break;
1185 case MemoryRepresentation::Int32():
1186 case MemoryRepresentation::Uint32(): {
1187 opcode = kS390_StoreWord32;
1188 const Operation& reverse_op = selector->Get(value);
1189 if (reverse_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32ReverseBytes>()) {
1190 opcode = kS390_StoreReverse32;
1191 value = selector->input_at(value, 0);
1192 }
1193 break;
1194 }
1195 case MemoryRepresentation::Int64():
1196 case MemoryRepresentation::Uint64(): {
1197 opcode = kS390_StoreWord64;
1198 const Operation& reverse_op = selector->Get(value);
1199 if (reverse_op.Is<Opmask::kWord64ReverseBytes>()) {
1200 opcode = kS390_StoreReverse64;
1201 value = selector->input_at(value, 0);
1202 }
1203 break;
1204 }
1205 case MemoryRepresentation::Float16():
1206 UNIMPLEMENTED();
1207 case MemoryRepresentation::Float32():
1208 opcode = kS390_StoreFloat32;
1209 break;
1210 case MemoryRepresentation::Float64():
1211 opcode = kS390_StoreDouble;
1212 break;
1213 case MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged():
1214 case MemoryRepresentation::TaggedPointer():
1215 case MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned():
1216 opcode = kS390_StoreCompressTagged;
1217 break;
1218 case MemoryRepresentation::AnyUncompressedTagged():
1219 case MemoryRepresentation::UncompressedTaggedPointer():
1220 case MemoryRepresentation::UncompressedTaggedSigned():
1221 opcode = kS390_StoreWord64;
1222 break;
1223 case MemoryRepresentation::Simd128(): {
1224 opcode = kS390_StoreSimd128;
1225 const Operation& reverse_op = selector->Get(value);
1226 // TODO(miladfarca): Rename this to `Opmask::kSimd128ReverseBytes` once
1227 // Turboshaft naming is decoupled from Turbofan naming.
1228 if (reverse_op.Is<Opmask::kSimd128Simd128ReverseBytes>()) {
1229 opcode = kS390_StoreReverseSimd128;
1230 value = selector->input_at(value, 0);
1231 }
1232 break;
1233 }
1234 case MemoryRepresentation::ProtectedPointer():
1235 // We never store directly to protected pointers from generated code.
1236 UNREACHABLE();
1237 case MemoryRepresentation::IndirectPointer():
1238 case MemoryRepresentation::SandboxedPointer():
1239 case MemoryRepresentation::Simd256():
1240 UNREACHABLE();
1241 }
1242
1243 InstructionOperand inputs[4];
1244 size_t input_count = 0;
1245 AddressingMode addressing_mode =
1246 g.GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(node, inputs, &input_count);
1247 InstructionCode code =
1248 opcode | AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode);
1249 InstructionOperand value_operand = g.UseRegister(value);
1250 inputs[input_count++] = value_operand;
1251 selector->Emit(code, 0, static_cast<InstructionOperand*>(nullptr),
1252 input_count, inputs);
1253 }
1254}
1255
1256static void VisitGeneralStore(
1257 InstructionSelectorT<TurbofanAdapter>* selector,
1258 typename TurbofanAdapter::node_t node, MachineRepresentation rep,
1259 WriteBarrierKind write_barrier_kind = kNoWriteBarrier) {
1260 using node_t = TurbofanAdapter::node_t;
1261 using optional_node_t = TurbofanAdapter::optional_node_t;
1262 S390OperandGeneratorT<TurbofanAdapter> g(selector);
1263
1264 auto store_view = selector->store_view(node);
1265 DCHECK_EQ(store_view.element_size_log2(), 0);
1266
1267 node_t base = store_view.base();
1268 optional_node_t index = store_view.index();
1269 node_t value = store_view.value();
1270 int32_t displacement = store_view.displacement();
1271
1272 if (write_barrier_kind != kNoWriteBarrier &&
1273 !v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) {
1274 DCHECK(CanBeTaggedOrCompressedPointer(rep));
1275 AddressingMode addressing_mode;
1276 InstructionOperand inputs[4];
1277 size_t input_count = 0;
1278 addressing_mode = g.GenerateMemoryOperandInputs(
1279 index, base, displacement, DisplacementMode::kPositiveDisplacement,
1280 inputs, &input_count,
1281 S390OperandGeneratorT<
1282 TurbofanAdapter>::RegisterUseKind::kUseUniqueRegister);
1283 DCHECK_LT(input_count, 4);
1284 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(value);
1285 RecordWriteMode record_write_mode =
1286 WriteBarrierKindToRecordWriteMode(write_barrier_kind);
1287 InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister(), g.TempRegister()};
1288 size_t const temp_count = arraysize(temps);
1289 InstructionCode code = kArchStoreWithWriteBarrier;
1290 code |= AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode);
1291 code |= RecordWriteModeField::encode(record_write_mode);
1292 selector->Emit(code, 0, nullptr, input_count, inputs, temp_count, temps);
1293 } else {
1294 ArchOpcode opcode;
1295 switch (rep) {
1296 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
1297 opcode = kS390_StoreFloat32;
1298 break;
1299 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
1300 opcode = kS390_StoreDouble;
1301 break;
1302 case MachineRepresentation::kBit: // Fall through.
1303 case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
1304 opcode = kS390_StoreWord8;
1305 break;
1306 case MachineRepresentation::kWord16:
1307 opcode = kS390_StoreWord16;
1308 break;
1309 case MachineRepresentation::kWord32: {
1310 opcode = kS390_StoreWord32;
1311 NodeMatcher m(value);
1312 if (m.IsWord32ReverseBytes()) {
1313 opcode = kS390_StoreReverse32;
1314 value = selector->input_at(value, 0);
1315 }
1316 break;
1317 }
1318 case MachineRepresentation::kCompressedPointer: // Fall through.
1319 case MachineRepresentation::kCompressed:
1320 case MachineRepresentation::kIndirectPointer: // Fall through.
1321 case MachineRepresentation::kSandboxedPointer: // Fall through.
1322#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
1323 opcode = kS390_StoreCompressTagged;
1324 break;
1325#else
1326 UNREACHABLE();
1327#endif
1328 case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned: // Fall through.
1329 case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer: // Fall through.
1330 case MachineRepresentation::kTagged:
1331 opcode = kS390_StoreCompressTagged;
1332 break;
1333 case MachineRepresentation::kWord64: {
1334 opcode = kS390_StoreWord64;
1335 NodeMatcher m(value);
1336 if (m.IsWord64ReverseBytes()) {
1337 opcode = kS390_StoreReverse64;
1338 value = selector->input_at(value, 0);
1339 }
1340 break;
1341 }
1342 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128: {
1343 opcode = kS390_StoreSimd128;
1344 NodeMatcher m(value);
1345 if (m.IsSimd128ReverseBytes()) {
1346 opcode = kS390_StoreReverseSimd128;
1347 value = selector->input_at(value, 0);
1348 }
1349 break;
1350 }
1351 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat16:
1352 UNIMPLEMENTED();
1353 case MachineRepresentation::kProtectedPointer: // Fall through.
1354 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd256: // Fall through.
1355 case MachineRepresentation::kMapWord: // Fall through.
1356 case MachineRepresentation::kNone:
1357 UNREACHABLE();
1358 }
1359 InstructionOperand inputs[4];
1360 size_t input_count = 0;
1361 AddressingMode addressing_mode =
1362 g.GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(node, inputs, &input_count);
1363 InstructionCode code =
1364 opcode | AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode);
1365 InstructionOperand value_operand = g.UseRegister(value);
1366 inputs[input_count++] = value_operand;
1367 selector->Emit(code, 0, static_cast<InstructionOperand*>(nullptr),
1368 input_count, inputs);
1369 }
1370}

1409template <typename Adapter>
1410void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitStackPointerGreaterThan(
1411 node_t node, FlagsContinuation* cont) {
1412 StackCheckKind kind;
1413 node_t value;
1414 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
1415 const auto& op =
1416 this->turboshaft_graph()
1417 ->Get(node)
1418 .template Cast<turboshaft::StackPointerGreaterThanOp>();
1419 kind = op.kind;
1420 value = op.stack_limit();
1421 } else {
1422 kind = StackCheckKindOf(node->op());
1423 value = node->InputAt(0);
1424 }
1425 InstructionCode opcode =
1426 kArchStackPointerGreaterThan | MiscField::encode(static_cast<int>(kind));
1427
1428 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
1429
1430 // No outputs.
1431 InstructionOperand* const outputs = nullptr;
1432 const int output_count = 0;
1433
1434 // Applying an offset to this stack check requires a temp register. Offsets
1435 // are only applied to the first stack check. If applying an offset, we must
1436 // ensure the input and temp registers do not alias, thus kUniqueRegister.
1437 InstructionOperand temps[] = {g.TempRegister()};
1438 const int temp_count = (kind == StackCheckKind::kJSFunctionEntry) ? 1 : 0;
1439 const auto register_mode = (kind == StackCheckKind::kJSFunctionEntry)
1440 ? OperandGenerator::kUniqueRegister
1441 : OperandGenerator::kRegister;
1442
1443 InstructionOperand inputs[] = {g.UseRegisterWithMode(value, register_mode)};
1444 static constexpr int input_count = arraysize(inputs);
1445
1446 EmitWithContinuation(opcode, output_count, outputs, input_count, inputs,
1447 temp_count, temps, cont);
1448}

1474template <>
1475void InstructionSelectorT<TurboshaftAdapter>::VisitWord64And(node_t node) {
1476 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
1477 S390OperandGeneratorT<TurboshaftAdapter> g(this);
1478
1479 const WordBinopOp& bitwise_and = Get(node).Cast<WordBinopOp>();
1480 int mb = 0;
1481 int me = 0;
1482 if (is_integer_constant(bitwise_and.right()) &&
1483 IsContiguousMask64(integer_constant(bitwise_and.right()), &mb, &me)) {
1484 int sh = 0;
1485 node_t left = bitwise_and.left();
1486 const Operation& lhs = Get(left);
1487 if ((lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord64ShiftRightLogical>() ||
1488 lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord64ShiftLeft>()) &&
1489 CanCover(node, left)) {
1490 // Try to absorb left/right shift into rldic
1491 int64_t shift_by;
1492 const ShiftOp& shift_op = lhs.Cast<ShiftOp>();
1493 if (MatchIntegralWord64Constant(shift_op.right(), &shift_by) &&
1494 base::IsInRange(shift_by, 0, 63)) {
1495 left = shift_op.left();
1496 sh = integer_constant(shift_op.right());
1497 if (lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord64ShiftRightLogical>()) {
1498 // Adjust the mask such that it doesn't include any rotated bits.
1499 if (mb > 63 - sh) mb = 63 - sh;
1500 sh = (64 - sh) & 0x3F;
1501 } else {
1502 // Adjust the mask such that it doesn't include any rotated bits.
1503 if (me < sh) me = sh;
1504 }
1505 }
1506 }
1507 if (mb >= me) {
1508 bool match = false;
1509 ArchOpcode opcode;
1510 int mask;
1511 if (me == 0) {
1512 match = true;
1513 opcode = kS390_RotLeftAndClearLeft64;
1514 mask = mb;
1515 } else if (mb == 63) {
1516 match = true;
1517 opcode = kS390_RotLeftAndClearRight64;
1518 mask = me;
1519 } else if (sh && me <= sh && lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord64ShiftLeft>()) {
1520 match = true;
1521 opcode = kS390_RotLeftAndClear64;
1522 mask = mb;
1523 }
1524 if (match && CpuFeatures::IsSupported(GENERAL_INSTR_EXT)) {
1525 Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(left),
1526 g.TempImmediate(sh), g.TempImmediate(mask));
1527 return;
1528 }
1529 }
1530 }
1531 VisitWord64BinOp(this, node, kS390_And64, And64OperandMode);
1532}

1763static inline bool TryMatchSignExtInt16OrInt8FromWord32Sar(
1764 InstructionSelectorT<TurboshaftAdapter>* selector,
1765 typename TurboshaftAdapter::node_t node) {
1766 S390OperandGeneratorT<TurboshaftAdapter> g(selector);
1767
1768 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
1769 const ShiftOp& sar = selector->Get(node).template Cast<ShiftOp>();
1770 const Operation& lhs = selector->Get(sar.left());
1771 if (selector->CanCover(node, sar.left()) &&
1772 lhs.Is<Opmask::kWord32ShiftLeft>()) {
1773 const ShiftOp& shl = lhs.Cast<ShiftOp>();
1774 if (selector->is_integer_constant(sar.right()) &&
1775 selector->is_integer_constant(shl.right())) {
1776 uint32_t sar_by = selector->integer_constant(sar.right());
1777 uint32_t shl_by = selector->integer_constant(shl.right());
1778 if ((sar_by == shl_by) && (sar_by == 16)) {
1779 bool canEliminateZeroExt =
1780 ProduceWord32Result<TurboshaftAdapter>(selector, shl.left());
1781 selector->Emit(kS390_SignExtendWord16ToInt32,
1782 canEliminateZeroExt ? g.DefineSameAsFirst(node)
1783 : g.DefineAsRegister(node),
1784 g.UseRegister(shl.left()),
1785 g.TempImmediate(!canEliminateZeroExt));
1786 return true;
1787 } else if ((sar_by == shl_by) && (sar_by == 24)) {
1788 bool canEliminateZeroExt =
1789 ProduceWord32Result<TurboshaftAdapter>(selector, shl.left());
1790 selector->Emit(kS390_SignExtendWord8ToInt32,
1791 canEliminateZeroExt ? g.DefineSameAsFirst(node)
1792 : g.DefineAsRegister(node),
1793 g.UseRegister(shl.left()),
1794 g.TempImmediate(!canEliminateZeroExt));
1795 return true;
1796 }
1797 }
1798 }
1799 return false;
1800}
1801
1802template <typename Adapter>
1803static inline bool TryMatchSignExtInt16OrInt8FromWord32Sar(
1804 InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector, typename Adapter::node_t node) {
1805 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
1806 Int32BinopMatcher m(node);
1807 if (selector->CanCover(node, m.left().node()) && m.left().IsWord32Shl()) {
1808 Int32BinopMatcher mleft(m.left().node());
1809 if (mleft.right().Is(16) && m.right().Is(16)) {
1810 bool canEliminateZeroExt =
1811 ProduceWord32Result<Adapter>(selector, mleft.left().node());
1812 selector->Emit(kS390_SignExtendWord16ToInt32,
1813 canEliminateZeroExt ? g.DefineSameAsFirst(node)
1814 : g.DefineAsRegister(node),
1815 g.UseRegister(mleft.left().node()),
1816 g.TempImmediate(!canEliminateZeroExt));
1817 return true;
1818 } else if (mleft.right().Is(24) && m.right().Is(24)) {
1819 bool canEliminateZeroExt =
1820 ProduceWord32Result<Adapter>(selector, mleft.left().node());
1821 selector->Emit(kS390_SignExtendWord8ToInt32,

1872template <typename Adapter>
1873void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitWord64ReverseBytes(node_t node) {
1874 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
1875 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
1876 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
1877 node_t input = this->Get(node).input(0);
1878 const Operation& input_op = this->Get(input);
1879 if (CanCover(node, input) && input_op.Is<LoadOp>()) {
1880 auto load = this->load_view(input);
1881 LoadRepresentation load_rep = load.loaded_rep();
1882 if (load_rep.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord64) {
1883 InstructionOperand outputs[] = {g.DefineAsRegister(node)};
1884 InstructionOperand inputs[3];
1885 size_t input_count = 0;
1886 AddressingMode mode =
1887 g.GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(input, inputs, &input_count);
1888 Emit(kS390_LoadReverse64 | AddressingModeField::encode(mode), 1,
1889 outputs, input_count, inputs);
1890 return;
1891 }
1892 }
1893 Emit(kS390_LoadReverse64RR, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
1894 g.UseRegister(this->input_at(node, 0)));
1895 } else {
1896 NodeMatcher input(node->InputAt(0));
1897 if (CanCover(node, input.node()) && input.IsLoad()) {
1898 LoadRepresentation load_rep = LoadRepresentationOf(input.node()->op());
1899 if (load_rep.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord64) {
1900 Node* base = input.node()->InputAt(0);
1901 Node* offset = input.node()->InputAt(1);
1902 Emit(kS390_LoadReverse64 | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_MRR),
1903 // TODO(miladfarca): one of the base and offset can be imm.
1904 g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(base),
1905 g.UseRegister(offset));
1906 return;
1907 }
1908 }
1909 Emit(kS390_LoadReverse64RR, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
1910 g.UseRegister(node->InputAt(0)));
1911 }

2000template <typename Adapter, class Matcher, ArchOpcode neg_opcode>
2001static inline bool TryMatchNegFromSub(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
2002 typename Adapter::node_t node) {
2003 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
2004 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
2005 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
2006 static_assert(neg_opcode == kS390_Neg32 || neg_opcode == kS390_Neg64,
2007 "Provided opcode is not a Neg opcode.");
2008 const WordBinopOp& sub_op =
2009 selector->Get(node).template Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2010 if (selector->MatchIntegralZero(sub_op.left())) {
2011 typename Adapter::node_t value = sub_op.right();
2012 bool doZeroExt = DoZeroExtForResult<Adapter>(selector, node);
2013 bool canEliminateZeroExt = ProduceWord32Result<Adapter>(selector, value);
2014 if (doZeroExt) {
2015 selector->Emit(neg_opcode,
2016 canEliminateZeroExt ? g.DefineSameAsFirst(node)
2017 : g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2018 g.UseRegister(value),
2019 g.TempImmediate(!canEliminateZeroExt));
2020 } else {
2021 selector->Emit(neg_opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2022 g.UseRegister(value));
2023 }
2024 return true;
2025 }
2026 return false;
2027
2028 } else {
2029 Matcher m(node);
2030 static_assert(neg_opcode == kS390_Neg32 || neg_opcode == kS390_Neg64,
2031 "Provided opcode is not a Neg opcode.");
2032 if (m.left().Is(0)) {
2033 Node* value = m.right().node();
2034 bool doZeroExt = DoZeroExtForResult<Adapter>(selector, node);
2035 bool canEliminateZeroExt = ProduceWord32Result<Adapter>(selector, value);
2036 if (doZeroExt) {
2037 selector->Emit(neg_opcode,
2038 canEliminateZeroExt ? g.DefineSameAsFirst(node)
2039 : g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2040 g.UseRegister(value),
2041 g.TempImmediate(!canEliminateZeroExt));
2042 } else {
2043 selector->Emit(neg_opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2044 g.UseRegister(value));
2045 }
2046 return true;
2047 }
2048 return false;
2049 }
2050}

2052template <typename Adapter, class Matcher, ArchOpcode shift_op>
2053bool TryMatchShiftFromMul(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
2054 typename Adapter::node_t node) {
2055 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
2056 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
2057 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
2058 const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
2059 const WordBinopOp& mul_op = op.Cast<WordBinopOp>();
2060 turboshaft::OpIndex left = mul_op.left();
2061 turboshaft::OpIndex right = mul_op.right();
2062 if (g.CanBeImmediate(right, OperandMode::kInt32Imm) &&
2063 base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(g.GetImmediate(right))) {
2064 int power = 63 - base::bits::CountLeadingZeros64(g.GetImmediate(right));
2065 bool doZeroExt = DoZeroExtForResult<Adapter>(selector, node);
2066 bool canEliminateZeroExt = ProduceWord32Result<Adapter>(selector, left);
2067 InstructionOperand dst = (doZeroExt && !canEliminateZeroExt &&
2068 CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS))
2069 ? g.DefineAsRegister(node)
2070 : g.DefineSameAsFirst(node);
2071
2072 if (doZeroExt) {
2073 selector->Emit(shift_op, dst, g.UseRegister(left),
2074 g.UseImmediate(power),
2075 g.TempImmediate(!canEliminateZeroExt));
2076 } else {
2077 selector->Emit(shift_op, dst, g.UseRegister(left),
2078 g.UseImmediate(power));
2079 }
2080 return true;
2081 }
2082 return false;
2083
2084 } else {
2085 Matcher m(node);
2086 Node* left = m.left().node();
2087 Node* right = m.right().node();
2088 if (g.CanBeImmediate(right, OperandMode::kInt32Imm) &&
2089 base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(g.GetImmediate(right))) {
2090 int power = 63 - base::bits::CountLeadingZeros64(g.GetImmediate(right));
2091 bool doZeroExt = DoZeroExtForResult<Adapter>(selector, node);
2092 bool canEliminateZeroExt = ProduceWord32Result<Adapter>(selector, left);
2093 InstructionOperand dst = (doZeroExt && !canEliminateZeroExt &&
2094 CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS))
2095 ? g.DefineAsRegister(node)
2096 : g.DefineSameAsFirst(node);
2097
2098 if (doZeroExt) {
2099 selector->Emit(shift_op, dst, g.UseRegister(left),
2100 g.UseImmediate(power),
2101 g.TempImmediate(!canEliminateZeroExt));
2102 } else {
2103 selector->Emit(shift_op, dst, g.UseRegister(left),
2104 g.UseImmediate(power));
2105 }
2106 return true;
2107 }
2108 return false;
2109 }
2110}

2200

2202 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(rhs);

2204 selector->EmitWithContinuation(kS390_Mul64WithOverflow, output_count, outputs,
2205 input_count, inputs, cont);

2208template <typename Adapter>
2209static inline bool TryMatchDoubleConstructFromInsert(
2210 InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector, typename Adapter::node_t node) {
2211 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
2212 UNIMPLEMENTED();
2213 } else {
2214 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
2215 Node* left = node->InputAt(0);
2216 Node* right = node->InputAt(1);
2217 Node* lo32 = nullptr;
2218 Node* hi32 = nullptr;
2219
2220 if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kFloat64InsertLowWord32) {
2221 lo32 = right;
2222 } else if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kFloat64InsertHighWord32) {
2223 hi32 = right;
2224 } else {
2225 return false; // doesn't match
2226 }
2227
2228 if (left->opcode() == IrOpcode::kFloat64InsertLowWord32) {
2229 lo32 = left->InputAt(1);
2230 } else if (left->opcode() == IrOpcode::kFloat64InsertHighWord32) {
2231 hi32 = left->InputAt(1);
2232 } else {
2233 return false; // doesn't match
2234 }
2235
2236 if (!lo32 || !hi32) return false; // doesn't match
2237
2238 selector->Emit(kS390_DoubleConstruct, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
2239 g.UseRegister(hi32), g.UseRegister(lo32));
2240 return true;
2241 }

2552template <typename Adapter>
2553static bool CompareLogical(FlagsContinuationT<Adapter>* cont) {
2554 switch (cont->condition()) {
2555 case kUnsignedLessThan:
2556 case kUnsignedGreaterThanOrEqual:
2557 case kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual:
2558 case kUnsignedGreaterThan:
2559 return true;
2560 default:
2561 return false;
2562 }
2563 UNREACHABLE();
2564}

2583// Shared routine for multiple word compare operations.
2584template <typename Adapter>
2585void VisitWordCompare(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
2586 typename Adapter::node_t node, InstructionCode opcode,
2587 FlagsContinuationT<Adapter>* cont,
2588 OperandModes immediate_mode) {
2589 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
2590 typename Adapter::node_t lhs = selector->input_at(node, 0);
2591 typename Adapter::node_t rhs = selector->input_at(node, 1);
2592
2593 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
2594 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
2595 const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
2596 DCHECK(op.Is<ComparisonOp>() || op.Is<Opmask::kWord32Sub>() ||
2597 op.Is<Opmask::kWord64Sub>());
2598 USE(op);
2599 } else {
2600 DCHECK(IrOpcode::IsComparisonOpcode(node->opcode()) ||
2601 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kInt32Sub ||
2602 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kInt64Sub);
2603 }
2604
2605 InstructionOperand inputs[8];
2606 InstructionOperand outputs[1];
2607 size_t input_count = 0;
2608 size_t output_count = 0;
2609
2610 // If one of the two inputs is an immediate, make sure it's on the right, or
2611 // if one of the two inputs is a memory operand, make sure it's on the left.
2612 int effect_level = selector->GetEffectLevel(node, cont);
2613
2614 if ((!g.CanBeImmediate(rhs, immediate_mode) &&
2615 g.CanBeImmediate(lhs, immediate_mode)) ||
2616 (!g.CanBeMemoryOperand(opcode, node, rhs, effect_level) &&
2617 g.CanBeMemoryOperand(opcode, node, lhs, effect_level))) {
2618 if (!selector->IsCommutative(node)) cont->Commute();
2619 std::swap(lhs, rhs);
2620 }
2621
2622 // check if compare with 0
2623 if (g.CanBeImmediate(rhs, immediate_mode) && g.GetImmediate(rhs) == 0) {
2624 DCHECK(opcode == kS390_Cmp32 || opcode == kS390_Cmp64);
2625 ArchOpcode load_and_test = (opcode == kS390_Cmp32)
2626 ? kS390_LoadAndTestWord32
2627 : kS390_LoadAndTestWord64;
2628 return VisitLoadAndTest(selector, load_and_test, node, lhs, cont, true);
2629 }
2630
2631 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(lhs);
2632 if (g.CanBeMemoryOperand(opcode, node, rhs, effect_level)) {
2633 // generate memory operand
2634 AddressingMode addressing_mode = g.GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(
2635 rhs, inputs, &input_count, OpcodeImmMode(opcode));
2636 opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode);
2637 } else if (g.CanBeImmediate(rhs, immediate_mode)) {
2638 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(rhs);
2639 } else {
2640 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseAnyExceptImmediate(rhs);
2641 }
2642
2643 DCHECK(input_count <= 8 && output_count <= 1);
2644 selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, output_count, outputs, input_count,
2645 inputs, cont);
2646}
2647
2648template <typename Adapter>
2649void VisitWord32Compare(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
2650 typename Adapter::node_t node,
2651 FlagsContinuationT<Adapter>* cont) {
2652 OperandModes mode = (CompareLogical(cont) ? OperandMode::kUint32Imm
2653 : OperandMode::kInt32Imm);
2654 VisitWordCompare(selector, node, kS390_Cmp32, cont, mode);
2655}
2656
2657template <typename Adapter>
2658void VisitWord64Compare(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
2659 typename Adapter::node_t node,
2660 FlagsContinuationT<Adapter>* cont) {
2661 OperandModes mode =
2662 (CompareLogical(cont) ? OperandMode::kUint32Imm : OperandMode::kInt32Imm);
2663 VisitWordCompare(selector, node, kS390_Cmp64, cont, mode);
2664}

2682void VisitTestUnderMask(InstructionSelectorT<TurboshaftAdapter>* selector,
2683 TurboshaftAdapter::node_t node,
2684 FlagsContinuationT<TurboshaftAdapter>* cont) {
2685 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
2686 const Operation& op = selector->Get(node);
2687 DCHECK(op.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>() ||
2688 op.Is<Opmask::kWord64BitwiseAnd>());
2689 USE(op);
2690
2691 ArchOpcode opcode;
2692 if (selector->Get(node).template TryCast<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>()) {
2693 opcode = kS390_Tst32;
2694 } else {
2695 opcode = kS390_Tst64;
2696 }
2697
2698 S390OperandGeneratorT<TurboshaftAdapter> g(selector);
2699 typename TurboshaftAdapter::node_t lhs = selector->input_at(node, 0);
2700 typename TurboshaftAdapter::node_t rhs = selector->input_at(node, 1);
2701 if (!g.CanBeImmediate(rhs, OperandMode::kUint32Imm) &&
2702 g.CanBeImmediate(lhs, OperandMode::kUint32Imm)) {
2703 std::swap(lhs, rhs);
2704 }
2705 VisitCompare(selector, opcode, g.UseRegister(lhs),
2706 g.UseOperand(rhs, OperandMode::kUint32Imm), cont);
2707}
2708
2709template <typename Adapter>
2710void VisitTestUnderMask(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector, Node* node,
2711 FlagsContinuationT<Adapter>* cont) {
2712 DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kWord32And ||
2713 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kWord64And);
2714 ArchOpcode opcode =
2715 (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kWord32And) ? kS390_Tst32 : kS390_Tst64;
2716 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
2717 Node* left = node->InputAt(0);
2718 Node* right = node->InputAt(1);
2719 if (!g.CanBeImmediate(right, OperandMode::kUint32Imm) &&
2720 g.CanBeImmediate(left, OperandMode::kUint32Imm)) {
2721 std::swap(left, right);
2722 }
2723 VisitCompare(selector, opcode, g.UseRegister(left),
2724 g.UseOperand(right, OperandMode::kUint32Imm), cont);
2725}
2726
2727template <typename Adapter>
2728void VisitLoadAndTest(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
2729 InstructionCode opcode, typename Adapter::node_t node,
2730 typename Adapter::node_t value,
2731 FlagsContinuationT<Adapter>* cont, bool discard_output) {
2732 static_assert(kS390_LoadAndTestFloat64 - kS390_LoadAndTestWord32 == 3,
2733 "LoadAndTest Opcode shouldn't contain other opcodes.");
2734 // TODO(john.yan): Add support for Float32/Float64.
2735 DCHECK(opcode >= kS390_LoadAndTestWord32 ||
2736 opcode <= kS390_LoadAndTestWord64);
2737
2738 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
2739 InstructionOperand inputs[8];
2740 InstructionOperand outputs[2];
2741 size_t input_count = 0;
2742 size_t output_count = 0;
2743 bool use_value = false;
2744
2745 int effect_level = selector->GetEffectLevel(node, cont);
2746
2747 if (g.CanBeMemoryOperand(opcode, node, value, effect_level)) {
2748 // generate memory operand
2749 AddressingMode addressing_mode =
2750 g.GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(value, inputs, &input_count);
2751 opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode);
2752 } else {
2753 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseAnyExceptImmediate(value);
2754 use_value = true;
2755 }
2756
2757 if (!discard_output && !use_value) {
2758 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsRegister(value);
2759 }
2760
2761 DCHECK(input_count <= 8 && output_count <= 2);
2762 selector->EmitWithContinuation(opcode, output_count, outputs, input_count,
2763 inputs, cont);
2764}
