2768// Shared routine for word comparisons against zero.
2769template <>
2770void InstructionSelectorT<TurboshaftAdapter>::VisitWordCompareZero(
2771 node_t user, node_t value, FlagsContinuation* cont) {
2772 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
2773
2774 // Try to combine with comparisons against 0 by simply inverting the branch.
2775 ConsumeEqualZero(&user, &value, cont);
2776
2777 FlagsCondition fc = cont->condition();
2778 if (CanCover(user, value)) {
2779 const Operation& value_op = this->Get(value);
2780 if (const ComparisonOp* comparison = value_op.TryCast<ComparisonOp>()) {
2781 if (comparison->kind == ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual) {
2782 switch (comparison->rep.MapTaggedToWord().value()) {
2783 case RegisterRepresentation::Word32(): {
2784 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kEqual);
2785 if (this->MatchIntegralZero(comparison->right())) {
2786 // Try to combine the branch with a comparison.
2787 if (CanCover(value, comparison->left())) {
2788 const Operation& left_op = this->Get(comparison->left());
2789 if (left_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32Sub>()) {
2790 return VisitWord32Compare(this, comparison->left(), cont);
2791 } else if (left_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>()) {
2792 return VisitTestUnderMask(this, comparison->left(), cont);
2793 }
2794 }
2795 }
2796 return VisitWord32Compare(this, value, cont);
2797 }
2798 case RegisterRepresentation::Word64(): {
2799 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kEqual);
2800 if (this->MatchIntegralZero(comparison->right())) {
2801 // Try to combine the branch with a comparison.
2802 if (CanCover(value, comparison->left())) {
2803 const Operation& left_op = this->Get(comparison->left());
2804 if (left_op.Is<Opmask::kWord64Sub>()) {
2805 return VisitWord64Compare(this, comparison->left(), cont);
2806 } else if (left_op.Is<Opmask::kWord64BitwiseAnd>()) {
2807 return VisitTestUnderMask(this, comparison->left(), cont);
2808 }
2809 }
2810 }
2811 return VisitWord64Compare(this, value, cont);
2812 }
2813 case RegisterRepresentation::Float32():
2814 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kEqual);
2815 return VisitFloat32Compare(this, value, cont);
2816 case RegisterRepresentation::Float64():
2817 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kEqual);
2818 return VisitFloat64Compare(this, value, cont);
2819 default:
2820 break;
2821 }
2822 } else {
2823 switch (comparison->rep.MapTaggedToWord().value()) {
2824 case RegisterRepresentation::Word32():
2825 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(
2826 GetComparisonFlagCondition(*comparison));
2827 return VisitWord32Compare(this, value, cont);
2828 case RegisterRepresentation::Word64():
2829 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(
2830 GetComparisonFlagCondition(*comparison));
2831 return VisitWord64Compare(this, value, cont);
2832 case RegisterRepresentation::Float32():
2833 switch (comparison->kind) {
2834 case ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan:
2835 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kUnsignedLessThan);
2836 return VisitFloat32Compare(this, value, cont);
2837 case ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual:
2838 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual);
2839 return VisitFloat32Compare(this, value, cont);
2840 default:
2841 UNREACHABLE();
2842 }
2843 case RegisterRepresentation::Float64():
2844 switch (comparison->kind) {
2845 case ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan:
2846 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kUnsignedLessThan);
2847 return VisitFloat64Compare(this, value, cont);
2848 case ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual:
2849 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual);
2850 return VisitFloat64Compare(this, value, cont);
2851 default:
2852 UNREACHABLE();
2853 }
2854 default:
2855 break;
2856 }
2857 }
2858 } else if (const ProjectionOp* projection =
2859 value_op.TryCast<ProjectionOp>()) {
2860 // Check if this is the overflow output projection of an
2861 // <Operation>WithOverflow node.
2862 if (projection->index == 1u) {
2863 // We cannot combine the <Operation>WithOverflow with this branch
2864 // unless the 0th projection (the use of the actual value of the
2865 // <Operation> is either nullptr, which means there's no use of the
2866 // actual value, or was already defined, which means it is scheduled
2867 // *AFTER* this branch).
2868 OpIndex node = projection->input();
2869 OpIndex result = FindProjection(node, 0);
2870 if (!result.valid() || IsDefined(result)) {
2871 if (const OverflowCheckedBinopOp* binop =
2872 TryCast<OverflowCheckedBinopOp>(node)) {
2873 const bool is64 = binop->rep == WordRepresentation::Word64();
2874 switch (binop->kind) {
2875 case OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedAdd:
2876 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kOverflow);
2877 if (is64) {
2878 return VisitWord64BinOp(this, node, kS390_Add64,
2879 AddOperandMode, cont);
2880 } else {
2881 return VisitWord32BinOp(this, node, kS390_Add32,
2882 AddOperandMode, cont);
2883 }
2884 case OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedSub:
2885 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kOverflow);
2886 if (is64) {
2887 return VisitWord64BinOp(this, node, kS390_Sub64,
2888 AddOperandMode, cont);
2889 } else {
2890 return VisitWord32BinOp(this, node, kS390_Sub32,
2891 AddOperandMode, cont);
2892 }
2893 case OverflowCheckedBinopOp::Kind::kSignedMul:
2894 if (is64) {
2895 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(
2896 CpuFeatures::IsSupported(MISC_INSTR_EXT2) ? kOverflow
2897 : kNotEqual);
2898 return EmitInt64MulWithOverflow(this, node, cont);
2899
2900 } else {
2901 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(MISC_INSTR_EXT2)) {
2902 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kOverflow);
2903 return VisitWord32BinOp(
2904 this, node, kS390_Mul32,
2905 OperandMode::kAllowRRR | OperandMode::kAllowRM, cont);
2906 } else {
2907 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kNotEqual);
2908 return VisitWord32BinOp(
2909 this, node, kS390_Mul32WithOverflow,
2910 OperandMode::kInt32Imm | OperandMode::kAllowDistinctOps,
2911 cont);
2912 }
2913 }
2914 default:
2915 break;
2916 }
2917 } else if (const OverflowCheckedUnaryOp* unop =
2918 TryCast<OverflowCheckedUnaryOp>(node)) {
2919 const bool is64 = unop->rep == WordRepresentation::Word64();
2920 switch (unop->kind) {
2921 case OverflowCheckedUnaryOp::Kind::kAbs:
2922 if (is64) {
2923 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kOverflow);
2924 return VisitWord64UnaryOp(this, node, kS390_Abs64,
2925 OperandMode::kNone, cont);
2926 } else {
2927 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kOverflow);
2928 return VisitWord32UnaryOp(this, node, kS390_Abs32,
2929 OperandMode::kNone, cont);
2930 }
2931 default:
2932 break;
2933 }
2934 }
2935 }
2936 }
2937 } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32Sub>()) {
2938 if (fc == kNotEqual || fc == kEqual)
2939 return VisitWord32Compare(this, value, cont);
2940 } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseAnd>()) {
2941 return VisitTestUnderMask(this, value, cont);
2942 } else if (value_op.Is<LoadOp>()) {
2943 auto load = this->load_view(value);
2944 LoadRepresentation load_rep = load.loaded_rep();
2945 switch (load_rep.representation()) {
2946 case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
2947 return VisitLoadAndTest(this, kS390_LoadAndTestWord32, user, value,
2948 cont);
2949 default:
2950 break;
2951 }
2952 } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseOr>()) {
2953 if (fc == kNotEqual || fc == kEqual)
2954 return VisitWord32BinOp(this, value, kS390_Or32, Or32OperandMode, cont);
2955 } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord32BitwiseXor>()) {
2956 if (fc == kNotEqual || fc == kEqual)
2957 return VisitWord32BinOp(this, value, kS390_Xor32, Xor32OperandMode,
2958 cont);
2959 } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord64Sub>()) {
2960 if (fc == kNotEqual || fc == kEqual)
2961 return VisitWord64Compare(this, value, cont);
2962 } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord64BitwiseAnd>()) {
2963 return VisitTestUnderMask(this, value, cont);
2964 } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord64BitwiseOr>()) {
2965 if (fc == kNotEqual || fc == kEqual)
2966 return VisitWord64BinOp(this, value, kS390_Or64, Or64OperandMode, cont);
2967 } else if (value_op.Is<Opmask::kWord64BitwiseXor>()) {
2968 if (fc == kNotEqual || fc == kEqual)
2969 return VisitWord64BinOp(this, value, kS390_Xor64, Xor64OperandMode,
2970 cont);
2971 } else if (value_op.Is<StackPointerGreaterThanOp>()) {
2972 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kStackPointerGreaterThanCondition);
2973 return VisitStackPointerGreaterThan(value, cont);
2974 }
2975 }
2976 // Branch could not be combined with a compare, emit LoadAndTest
2977 VisitLoadAndTest(this, kS390_LoadAndTestWord32, user, value, cont, true);
2978}
2979
2980// Shared routine for word comparisons against zero.
2981template <typename Adapter>
2982void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitWordCompareZero(
2983 node_t user, node_t value, FlagsContinuation* cont) {
2984 // Try to combine with comparisons against 0 by simply inverting the branch.
2985 while (value->opcode() == IrOpcode::kWord32Equal && CanCover(user, value)) {
2986 Int32BinopMatcher m(value);
2987 if (!m.right().Is(0)) break;
2988
2989 user = value;
2990 value = m.left().node();
2991 cont->Negate();
2992 }
2993
2994 FlagsCondition fc = cont->condition();
2995 if (CanCover(user, value)) {
2996 switch (value->opcode()) {
2997 case IrOpcode::kWord32Equal: {
2998 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kEqual);
2999 Int32BinopMatcher m(value);
3000 if (m.right().Is(0)) {
3001 // Try to combine the branch with a comparison.
3002 Node* const user = m.node();
3003 Node* const value = m.left().node();
3004 if (CanCover(user, value)) {
3005 switch (value->opcode()) {
3006 case IrOpcode::kInt32Sub:
3007 return VisitWord32Compare(this, value, cont);
3008 case IrOpcode::kWord32And:
3009 return VisitTestUnderMask(this, value, cont);
3010 default:
3011 break;
3012 }
3013 }
3014 }
3015 return VisitWord32Compare(this, value, cont);
3016 }
3017 case IrOpcode::kInt32LessThan:
3018 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kSignedLessThan);
3019 return VisitWord32Compare(this, value, cont);
3020 case IrOpcode::kInt32LessThanOrEqual:
3021 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kSignedLessThanOrEqual);
3022 return VisitWord32Compare(this, value, cont);
3023 case IrOpcode::kUint32LessThan:
3024 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kUnsignedLessThan);
3025 return VisitWord32Compare(this, value, cont);
3026 case IrOpcode::kUint32LessThanOrEqual:
3027 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual);
3028 return VisitWord32Compare(this, value, cont);
3029 case IrOpcode::kWord64Equal: {
3030 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kEqual);
3031 Int64BinopMatcher m(value);
3032 if (m.right().Is(0)) {
3033 // Try to combine the branch with a comparison.
3034 Node* const user = m.node();
3035 Node* const value = m.left().node();
3036 if (CanCover(user, value)) {
3037 switch (value->opcode()) {
3038 case IrOpcode::kInt64Sub:
3039 return VisitWord64Compare(this, value, cont);
3040 case IrOpcode::kWord64And:
3041 return VisitTestUnderMask(this, value, cont);
3042 default:
3043 break;
3044 }
3045 }
3046 }
3047 return VisitWord64Compare(this, value, cont);
3048 }
3049 case IrOpcode::kInt64LessThan:
3050 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kSignedLessThan);
3051 return VisitWord64Compare(this, value, cont);
3052 case IrOpcode::kInt64LessThanOrEqual:
3053 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kSignedLessThanOrEqual);
3054 return VisitWord64Compare(this, value, cont);
3055 case IrOpcode::kUint64LessThan:
3056 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kUnsignedLessThan);
3057 return VisitWord64Compare(this, value, cont);
3058 case IrOpcode::kUint64LessThanOrEqual:
3059 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual);
3060 return VisitWord64Compare(this, value, cont);
3061 case IrOpcode::kFloat32Equal:
3062 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kEqual);
3063 return VisitFloat32Compare(this, value, cont);
3064 case IrOpcode::kFloat32LessThan:
3065 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kUnsignedLessThan);
3066 return VisitFloat32Compare(this, value, cont);
3067 case IrOpcode::kFloat32LessThanOrEqual:
3068 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual);
3069 return VisitFloat32Compare(this, value, cont);
3070 case IrOpcode::kFloat64Equal:
3071 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kEqual);
3072 return VisitFloat64Compare(this, value, cont);
3073 case IrOpcode::kFloat64LessThan:
3074 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kUnsignedLessThan);
3075 return VisitFloat64Compare(this, value, cont);
3076 case IrOpcode::kFloat64LessThanOrEqual:
3077 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual);
3078 return VisitFloat64Compare(this, value, cont);
3079 case IrOpcode::kProjection:
3080 // Check if this is the overflow output projection of an
3081 // <Operation>WithOverflow node.
3082 if (ProjectionIndexOf(value->op()) == 1u) {
3083 // We cannot combine the <Operation>WithOverflow with this branch
3084 // unless the 0th projection (the use of the actual value of the
3085 // <Operation> is either nullptr, which means there's no use of the
3086 // actual value, or was already defined, which means it is scheduled
3087 // *AFTER* this branch).
3088 Node* const node = value->InputAt(0);
3089 Node* const result = NodeProperties::FindProjection(node, 0);
3090 if (result == nullptr || IsDefined(result)) {
3091 switch (node->opcode()) {
3092 case IrOpcode::kInt32AddWithOverflow:
3093 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kOverflow);
3094 return VisitWord32BinOp(this, node, kS390_Add32, AddOperandMode,
3095 cont);
3096 case IrOpcode::kInt32SubWithOverflow:
3097 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kOverflow);
3098 return VisitWord32BinOp(this, node, kS390_Sub32, SubOperandMode,
3099 cont);
3100 case IrOpcode::kInt32MulWithOverflow:
3101 if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(MISC_INSTR_EXT2)) {
3102 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kOverflow);
3103 return VisitWord32BinOp(
3104 this, node, kS390_Mul32,
3105 OperandMode::kAllowRRR | OperandMode::kAllowRM, cont);
3106 } else {
3107 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kNotEqual);
3108 return VisitWord32BinOp(
3109 this, node, kS390_Mul32WithOverflow,
3110 OperandMode::kInt32Imm | OperandMode::kAllowDistinctOps,
3111 cont);
3112 }
3113 case IrOpcode::kInt32AbsWithOverflow:
3114 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kOverflow);
3115 return VisitWord32UnaryOp(this, node, kS390_Abs32,
3116 OperandMode::kNone, cont);
3117 case IrOpcode::kInt64AbsWithOverflow:
3118 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kOverflow);
3119 return VisitWord64UnaryOp(this, node, kS390_Abs64,
3120 OperandMode::kNone, cont);
3121 case IrOpcode::kInt64AddWithOverflow:
3122 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kOverflow);
3123 return VisitWord64BinOp(this, node, kS390_Add64, AddOperandMode,
3124 cont);
3125 case IrOpcode::kInt64SubWithOverflow:
3126 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kOverflow);
3127 return VisitWord64BinOp(this, node, kS390_Sub64, SubOperandMode,
3128 cont);
3129 case IrOpcode::kInt64MulWithOverflow:
3130 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(
3131 CpuFeatures::IsSupported(MISC_INSTR_EXT2) ? kOverflow
3132 : kNotEqual);
3133 return EmitInt64MulWithOverflow(this, node, cont);
3134 default:
3135 break;
3136 }
3137 }
3138 }
3139 break;
3140 case IrOpcode::kInt32Sub:
3141 if (fc == kNotEqual || fc == kEqual)
3142 return VisitWord32Compare(this, value, cont);
3143 break;
3144 case IrOpcode::kWord32And:
3145 return VisitTestUnderMask(this, value, cont);
3146 case IrOpcode::kLoad:
3147 case IrOpcode::kLoadImmutable: {
3148 LoadRepresentation load_rep = LoadRepresentationOf(value->op());
3149 switch (load_rep.representation()) {
3150 case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
3151 return VisitLoadAndTest(this, kS390_LoadAndTestWord32, user, value,
3152 cont);
3153 default:
3154 break;
3155 }
3156 break;
3157 }
3158 case IrOpcode::kInt32Add:
3159 // can't handle overflow case.
3160 break;
3161 case IrOpcode::kWord32Or:
3162 if (fc == kNotEqual || fc == kEqual)
3163 return VisitWord32BinOp(this, value, kS390_Or32, Or32OperandMode,
3164 cont);
3165 break;
3166 case IrOpcode::kWord32Xor:
3167 if (fc == kNotEqual || fc == kEqual)
3168 return VisitWord32BinOp(this, value, kS390_Xor32, Xor32OperandMode,
3169 cont);
3170 break;
3171 case IrOpcode::kWord32Sar:
3172 case IrOpcode::kWord32Shl:
3173 case IrOpcode::kWord32Shr:
3174 case IrOpcode::kWord32Ror:
3175 // doesn't generate cc, so ignore.
3176 break;
3177 case IrOpcode::kInt64Sub:
3178 if (fc == kNotEqual || fc == kEqual)
3179 return VisitWord64Compare(this, value, cont);
3180 break;
3181 case IrOpcode::kWord64And:
3182 return VisitTestUnderMask(this, value, cont);
3183 case IrOpcode::kInt64Add:
3184 // can't handle overflow case.
3185 break;
3186 case IrOpcode::kWord64Or:
3187 if (fc == kNotEqual || fc == kEqual)
3188 return VisitWord64BinOp(this, value, kS390_Or64, Or64OperandMode,
3189 cont);
3190 break;
3191 case IrOpcode::kWord64Xor:
3192 if (fc == kNotEqual || fc == kEqual)
3193 return VisitWord64BinOp(this, value, kS390_Xor64, Xor64OperandMode,
3194 cont);
3195 break;
3196 case IrOpcode::kWord64Sar:
3197 case IrOpcode::kWord64Shl:
3198 case IrOpcode::kWord64Shr:
3199 case IrOpcode::kWord64Ror:
3200 // doesn't generate cc, so ignore
3201 break;
3202 case IrOpcode::kStackPointerGreaterThan:
3203 cont->OverwriteAndNegateIfEqual(kStackPointerGreaterThanCondition);
3204 return VisitStackPointerGreaterThan(value, cont);
3205 default:
3206 break;
3207 }
3208 }
3209
3210 // Branch could not be combined with a compare, emit LoadAndTest
3211 VisitLoadAndTest(this, kS390_LoadAndTestWord32, user, value, cont, true);
3212}

3214template <typename Adapter>
3215void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitSwitch(node_t node,
3216 const SwitchInfo& sw) {
3217 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
3218 InstructionOperand value_operand = g.UseRegister(this->input_at(node, 0));
3219
3220 // Emit either ArchTableSwitch or ArchBinarySearchSwitch.
3221 if (enable_switch_jump_table_ ==
3222 InstructionSelector::kEnableSwitchJumpTable) {
3223 static const size_t kMaxTableSwitchValueRange = 2 << 16;
3224 size_t table_space_cost = 4 + sw.value_range();
3225 size_t table_time_cost = 3;
3226 size_t lookup_space_cost = 3 + 2 * sw.case_count();
3227 size_t lookup_time_cost = sw.case_count();
3228 if (sw.case_count() > 0 &&
3229 table_space_cost + 3 * table_time_cost <=
3230 lookup_space_cost + 3 * lookup_time_cost &&
3231 sw.min_value() > std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min() &&
3232 sw.value_range() <= kMaxTableSwitchValueRange) {
3233 InstructionOperand index_operand = value_operand;
3234 if (sw.min_value()) {
3235 index_operand = g.TempRegister();
3236 Emit(kS390_Lay | AddressingModeField::encode(kMode_MRI), index_operand,
3237 value_operand, g.TempImmediate(-sw.min_value()));
3238 }
3239 InstructionOperand index_operand_zero_ext = g.TempRegister();
3240 Emit(kS390_Uint32ToUint64, index_operand_zero_ext, index_operand);
3241 index_operand = index_operand_zero_ext;
3242 // Generate a table lookup.
3243 return EmitTableSwitch(sw, index_operand);
3244 }
3245 }
3246
3247 // Generate a tree of conditional jumps.
3248 return EmitBinarySearchSwitch(sw, value_operand);
3249}

3416template <typename Adapter>
3417void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::EmitPrepareArguments(
3418 ZoneVector<PushParameter>* arguments, const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor,
3419 node_t node) {
3420 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
3421
3422 // Prepare for C function call.
3423 if (call_descriptor->IsCFunctionCall()) {
3424 Emit(kArchPrepareCallCFunction | MiscField::encode(static_cast<int>(
3425 call_descriptor->ParameterCount())),
3426 0, nullptr, 0, nullptr);
3427
3428 // Poke any stack arguments.
3429 int slot = kStackFrameExtraParamSlot;
3430 for (PushParameter input : (*arguments)) {
3431 if (!this->valid(input.node)) continue;
3432 Emit(kS390_StoreToStackSlot, g.NoOutput(), g.UseRegister(input.node),
3433 g.TempImmediate(slot));
3434 ++slot;
3435 }
3436 } else {
3437 // Push any stack arguments.
3438 int stack_decrement = 0;
3439 for (PushParameter input : base::Reversed(*arguments)) {
3440 stack_decrement += kSystemPointerSize;
3441 // Skip any alignment holes in pushed nodes.
3442 if (!this->valid(input.node)) continue;
3443 InstructionOperand decrement = g.UseImmediate(stack_decrement);
3444 stack_decrement = 0;
3445 Emit(kS390_Push, g.NoOutput(), decrement, g.UseRegister(input.node));
3446 }
3447 }
3448}

3453 Emit(kArchNop, g.NoOutput());

3478template <typename Adapter>
3479void VisitAtomicExchange(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
3480 typename Adapter::node_t node, ArchOpcode opcode,
3481 AtomicWidth width) {
3482 using node_t = typename Adapter::node_t;
3483 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
3484 auto atomic_op = selector->atomic_rmw_view(node);
3485 node_t base = atomic_op.base();
3486 node_t index = atomic_op.index();
3487 node_t value = atomic_op.value();
3488
3489 AddressingMode addressing_mode = kMode_MRR;
3490 InstructionOperand inputs[3];
3491 size_t input_count = 0;
3492 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(base);
3493 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(index);
3494 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(value);
3495 InstructionOperand outputs[1];
3496 outputs[0] = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
3497 InstructionCode code = opcode | AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode) |
3498 AtomicWidthField::encode(width);
3499 selector->Emit(code, 1, outputs, input_count, inputs);
3500}

3585template <typename Adapter>
3586void VisitAtomicCompareExchange(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
3587 typename Adapter::node_t node,
3588 ArchOpcode opcode, AtomicWidth width) {
3589 using node_t = typename Adapter::node_t;
3590 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
3591 auto atomic_op = selector->atomic_rmw_view(node);
3592 node_t base = atomic_op.base();
3593 node_t index = atomic_op.index();
3594 node_t old_value = atomic_op.expected();
3595 node_t new_value = atomic_op.value();
3596
3597 InstructionOperand inputs[4];
3598 size_t input_count = 0;
3599 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(old_value);
3600 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(new_value);
3601 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(base);
3602
3603 AddressingMode addressing_mode;
3604 if (g.CanBeImmediate(index, OperandMode::kInt20Imm)) {
3605 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(index);
3606 addressing_mode = kMode_MRI;
3607 } else {
3608 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(index);
3609 addressing_mode = kMode_MRR;
3610 }
3611
3612 InstructionOperand outputs[1];
3613 size_t output_count = 0;
3614 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineSameAsFirst(node);
3615
3616 InstructionCode code = opcode | AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode) |
3617 AtomicWidthField::encode(width);
3618 selector->Emit(code, output_count, outputs, input_count, inputs);
3619}

3704template <typename Adapter>
3705void VisitAtomicBinop(InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>* selector,
3706 typename Adapter::node_t node, ArchOpcode opcode,
3707 AtomicWidth width) {
3708 using node_t = typename Adapter::node_t;
3709 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(selector);
3710 auto atomic_op = selector->atomic_rmw_view(node);
3711 node_t base = atomic_op.base();
3712 node_t index = atomic_op.index();
3713 node_t value = atomic_op.value();
3714
3715 InstructionOperand inputs[3];
3716 size_t input_count = 0;
3717 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(base);
3718
3719 AddressingMode addressing_mode;
3720 if (g.CanBeImmediate(index, OperandMode::kInt20Imm)) {
3721 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(index);
3722 addressing_mode = kMode_MRI;
3723 } else {
3724 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(index);
3725 addressing_mode = kMode_MRR;
3726 }
3727
3728 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseUniqueRegister(value);
3729
3730 InstructionOperand outputs[1];
3731 size_t output_count = 0;
3732 outputs[output_count++] = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
3733
3734 InstructionOperand temps[1];
3735 size_t temp_count = 0;
3736 temps[temp_count++] = g.TempRegister();
3737
3738 InstructionCode code = opcode | AddressingModeField::encode(addressing_mode) |
3739 AtomicWidthField::encode(width);
3740 selector->Emit(code, output_count, outputs, input_count, inputs, temp_count,
3741 temps);
3742}

4239#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4240template <typename Adapter>
4241void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitI8x16Shuffle(node_t node) {
4242 uint8_t shuffle[kSimd128Size];
4243 bool is_swizzle;
4244 // TODO(nicohartmann@): Properly use view here once Turboshaft support is
4245 // implemented.
4246 auto view = this->simd_shuffle_view(node);
4247 CanonicalizeShuffle(view, shuffle, &is_swizzle);
4248 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
4249 node_t input0 = view.input(0);
4250 node_t input1 = view.input(1);
4251 // Remap the shuffle indices to match IBM lane numbering.
4252 int max_index = 15;
4253 int total_lane_count = 2 * kSimd128Size;
4254 uint8_t shuffle_remapped[kSimd128Size];
4255 for (int i = 0; i < kSimd128Size; i++) {
4256 uint8_t current_index = shuffle[i];
4257 shuffle_remapped[i] =
4258 (current_index <= max_index
4259 ? max_index - current_index
4260 : total_lane_count - current_index + max_index);
4261 }
4262 Emit(kS390_I8x16Shuffle, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(input0),
4263 g.UseRegister(input1),
4264 g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(shuffle_remapped)),
4265 g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(shuffle_remapped + 4)),
4266 g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(shuffle_remapped + 8)),
4267 g.UseImmediate(wasm::SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes(shuffle_remapped + 12)));
4268}

4313// This is a replica of SimdShuffle::Pack4Lanes. However, above function will
4314// not be available on builds with webassembly disabled, hence we need to have
4315// it declared locally as it is used on other visitors such as S128Const.
4316static int32_t Pack4Lanes(const uint8_t* shuffle) {
4317 int32_t result = 0;
4318 for (int i = 3; i >= 0; --i) {
4319 result <<= 8;
4320 result |= shuffle[i];
4321 }
4322 return result;
4323}

4325template <typename Adapter>
4326void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitS128Const(node_t node) {
4327 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
4328 uint32_t val[kSimd128Size / sizeof(uint32_t)];
4329 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
4330 const turboshaft::Simd128ConstantOp& constant =
4331 this->Get(node).template Cast<turboshaft::Simd128ConstantOp>();
4332 memcpy(val, constant.value, kSimd128Size);
4333 } else {
4334 memcpy(val, S128ImmediateParameterOf(node->op()).data(), kSimd128Size);
4335 }
4336 // If all bytes are zeros, avoid emitting code for generic constants.
4337 bool all_zeros = !(val[0] || val[1] || val[2] || val[3]);
4338 bool all_ones = val[0] == UINT32_MAX && val[1] == UINT32_MAX &&
4339 val[2] == UINT32_MAX && val[3] == UINT32_MAX;
4340 InstructionOperand dst = g.DefineAsRegister(node);
4341 if (all_zeros) {
4342 Emit(kS390_S128Zero, dst);
4343 } else if (all_ones) {
4344 Emit(kS390_S128AllOnes, dst);
4345 } else {
4346 // We have to use Pack4Lanes to reverse the bytes (lanes) on BE,
4347 // Which in this case is ineffective on LE.
4348 Emit(
4349 kS390_S128Const, dst,
4350 g.UseImmediate(Pack4Lanes(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(&val[0]))),
4351 g.UseImmediate(Pack4Lanes(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(&val[0]) + 4)),
4352 g.UseImmediate(Pack4Lanes(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(&val[0]) + 8)),
4353 g.UseImmediate(Pack4Lanes(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(&val[0]) + 12)));
4354 }
4355}

4372template <typename Adapter>
4373void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::EmitPrepareResults(
4374 ZoneVector<PushParameter>* results, const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor,
4375 node_t node) {
4376 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
4377
4378 for (PushParameter output : *results) {
4379 if (!output.location.IsCallerFrameSlot()) continue;
4380 // Skip any alignment holes in nodes.
4381 if (this->valid(output.node)) {
4382 DCHECK(!call_descriptor->IsCFunctionCall());
4383 if (output.location.GetType() == MachineType::Float32()) {
4384 MarkAsFloat32(output.node);
4385 } else if (output.location.GetType() == MachineType::Float64()) {
4386 MarkAsFloat64(output.node);
4387 } else if (output.location.GetType() == MachineType::Simd128()) {
4388 MarkAsSimd128(output.node);
4389 }
4390 int offset = call_descriptor->GetOffsetToReturns();
4391 int reverse_slot = -output.location.GetLocation() - offset;
4392 Emit(kS390_Peek, g.DefineAsRegister(output.node),
4393 g.UseImmediate(reverse_slot));
4394 }
4395 }
4396}

4398template <typename Adapter>
4399void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitLoadLane(node_t node) {
4400 InstructionCode opcode;
4401 int32_t lane;
4402 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
4403 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
4404 const Simd128LaneMemoryOp& load =
4405 this->Get(node).template Cast<Simd128LaneMemoryOp>();
4406 lane = load.lane;
4407 switch (load.lane_kind) {
4408 case Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k8:
4409 opcode = kS390_S128Load8Lane;
4410 break;
4411 case Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k16:
4412 opcode = kS390_S128Load16Lane;
4413 break;
4414 case Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k32:
4415 opcode = kS390_S128Load32Lane;
4416 break;
4417 case Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k64:
4418 opcode = kS390_S128Load64Lane;
4419 break;
4420 }
4421 } else {
4422 LoadLaneParameters params = LoadLaneParametersOf(node->op());
4423 lane = params.laneidx;
4424 if (params.rep == MachineType::Int8()) {
4425 opcode = kS390_S128Load8Lane;
4426 } else if (params.rep == MachineType::Int16()) {
4427 opcode = kS390_S128Load16Lane;
4428 } else if (params.rep == MachineType::Int32()) {
4429 opcode = kS390_S128Load32Lane;
4430 } else if (params.rep == MachineType::Int64()) {
4431 opcode = kS390_S128Load64Lane;
4432 } else {
4433 UNREACHABLE();
4434 }
4435 }
4436 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
4437 InstructionOperand outputs[] = {g.DefineSameAsFirst(node)};
4438 InstructionOperand inputs[5];
4439 size_t input_count = 0;
4440
4441 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(this->input_at(node, 2));
4442 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(lane);
4443
4444 AddressingMode mode =
4445 g.GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(node, inputs, &input_count);
4446 opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(mode);
4447 Emit(opcode, 1, outputs, input_count, inputs);
4448}

4450template <typename Adapter>
4451void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitLoadTransform(node_t node) {
4452 ArchOpcode opcode;
4453 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
4454 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
4455 const Simd128LoadTransformOp& op =
4456 this->Get(node).template Cast<Simd128LoadTransformOp>();
4457 switch (op.transform_kind) {
4458 case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k8Splat:
4459 opcode = kS390_S128Load8Splat;
4460 break;
4461 case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k16Splat:
4462 opcode = kS390_S128Load16Splat;
4463 break;
4464 case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k32Splat:
4465 opcode = kS390_S128Load32Splat;
4466 break;
4467 case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k64Splat:
4468 opcode = kS390_S128Load64Splat;
4469 break;
4470 case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k8x8S:
4471 opcode = kS390_S128Load8x8S;
4472 break;
4473 case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k8x8U:
4474 opcode = kS390_S128Load8x8U;
4475 break;
4476 case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k16x4S:
4477 opcode = kS390_S128Load16x4S;
4478 break;
4479 case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k16x4U:
4480 opcode = kS390_S128Load16x4U;
4481 break;
4482 case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k32x2S:
4483 opcode = kS390_S128Load32x2S;
4484 break;
4485 case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k32x2U:
4486 opcode = kS390_S128Load32x2U;
4487 break;
4488 case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k32Zero:
4489 opcode = kS390_S128Load32Zero;
4490 break;
4491 case Simd128LoadTransformOp::TransformKind::k64Zero:
4492 opcode = kS390_S128Load64Zero;
4493 break;
4494 default:
4495 UNIMPLEMENTED();
4496 }
4497 } else {
4498 LoadTransformParameters params = LoadTransformParametersOf(node->op());
4499 switch (params.transformation) {
4500 case LoadTransformation::kS128Load8Splat:
4501 opcode = kS390_S128Load8Splat;
4502 break;
4503 case LoadTransformation::kS128Load16Splat:
4504 opcode = kS390_S128Load16Splat;
4505 break;
4506 case LoadTransformation::kS128Load32Splat:
4507 opcode = kS390_S128Load32Splat;
4508 break;
4509 case LoadTransformation::kS128Load64Splat:
4510 opcode = kS390_S128Load64Splat;
4511 break;
4512 case LoadTransformation::kS128Load8x8S:
4513 opcode = kS390_S128Load8x8S;
4514 break;
4515 case LoadTransformation::kS128Load8x8U:
4516 opcode = kS390_S128Load8x8U;
4517 break;
4518 case LoadTransformation::kS128Load16x4S:
4519 opcode = kS390_S128Load16x4S;
4520 break;
4521 case LoadTransformation::kS128Load16x4U:
4522 opcode = kS390_S128Load16x4U;
4523 break;
4524 case LoadTransformation::kS128Load32x2S:
4525 opcode = kS390_S128Load32x2S;
4526 break;
4527 case LoadTransformation::kS128Load32x2U:
4528 opcode = kS390_S128Load32x2U;
4529 break;
4530 case LoadTransformation::kS128Load32Zero:
4531 opcode = kS390_S128Load32Zero;
4532 break;
4533 case LoadTransformation::kS128Load64Zero:
4534 opcode = kS390_S128Load64Zero;
4535 break;
4536 default:
4537 UNREACHABLE();
4538 }
4539 }
4540 VisitLoad(node, node, opcode);
4541}
4542
4543template <typename Adapter>
4544void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitStoreLane(node_t node) {
4545 InstructionCode opcode = kArchNop;
4546 int32_t lane;
4547 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
4548 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
4549 const Simd128LaneMemoryOp& store =
4550 this->Get(node).template Cast<Simd128LaneMemoryOp>();
4551 lane = store.lane;
4552 switch (store.lane_kind) {
4553 case Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k8:
4554 opcode = kS390_S128Store8Lane;
4555 break;
4556 case Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k16:
4557 opcode = kS390_S128Store16Lane;
4558 break;
4559 case Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k32:
4560 opcode = kS390_S128Store32Lane;
4561 break;
4562 case Simd128LaneMemoryOp::LaneKind::k64:
4563 opcode = kS390_S128Store64Lane;
4564 break;
4565 }
4566 } else {
4567 StoreLaneParameters params = StoreLaneParametersOf(node->op());
4568 lane = params.laneidx;
4569 if (params.rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord8) {
4570 opcode = kS390_S128Store8Lane;
4571 } else if (params.rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord16) {
4572 opcode = kS390_S128Store16Lane;
4573 } else if (params.rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord32) {
4574 opcode = kS390_S128Store32Lane;
4575 } else if (params.rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord64) {
4576 opcode = kS390_S128Store64Lane;
4577 } else {
4578 UNREACHABLE();
4579 }
4580 }
4581 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
4582 InstructionOperand inputs[5];
4583 size_t input_count = 0;
4584
4585 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseRegister(this->input_at(node, 2));
4586 inputs[input_count++] = g.UseImmediate(lane);
4587
4588 AddressingMode mode =
4589 g.GetEffectiveAddressMemoryOperand(node, inputs, &input_count);
4590 opcode |= AddressingModeField::encode(mode);
4591 Emit(opcode, 0, nullptr, input_count, inputs);
4592}

4612template <typename Adapter>
4613void InstructionSelectorT<Adapter>::VisitTruncateFloat32ToInt32(node_t node) {
4614 S390OperandGeneratorT<Adapter> g(this);
4615 if constexpr (Adapter::IsTurboshaft) {
4616 using namespace turboshaft; // NOLINT(build/namespaces)
4617 const Operation& op = this->Get(node);
4618 InstructionCode opcode = kS390_Float32ToInt32;
4619 if (op.Is<Opmask::kTruncateFloat32ToInt32OverflowToMin>()) {
4620 opcode |= MiscField::encode(true);
4621 }
4622 Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node),
4623 g.UseRegister(this->input_at(node, 0)));
4624 } else {
4625 InstructionCode opcode = kS390_Float32ToInt32;
4626 TruncateKind kind = OpParameter<TruncateKind>(node->op());
4627 if (kind == TruncateKind::kSetOverflowToMin) {
4628 opcode |= MiscField::encode(true);
4629 }
4630
4631 Emit(opcode, g.DefineAsRegister(node), g.UseRegister(node->InputAt(0)));
4632 }
4633}
